1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,590
Do we just take one?

2
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:09,759
-What's with the scissors?
-It's scary.

3
00:00:11,094 --> 00:00:13,680
I'm confused
about the scissors and the book.

4
00:00:14,472 --> 00:00:16,641
Whose item is <i>The Art of Loving</i>?

5
00:00:17,684 --> 00:00:19,269
What are those scissors?

6
00:00:19,352 --> 00:00:20,729
-I know.
-The scissors are…

7
00:00:20,812 --> 00:00:23,148
I don't even know
what that item in the middle is.

8
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:25,316
It's a metronome.

9
00:00:27,068 --> 00:00:28,903
Looks like she's figured it out.

10
00:00:29,487 --> 00:00:30,822
The tooth is the only obvious one.

11
00:00:36,327 --> 00:00:37,203
It was too…

12
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:40,832
Even I felt it was too obviously mine.

13
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:42,917
So I was embarrassed.

14
00:00:43,668 --> 00:00:45,170
Actually, I…

15
00:00:45,754 --> 00:00:48,840
<i>collect plush toys as a hobby.</i>

16
00:00:48,923 --> 00:00:50,133
<i>That's why I brought it.</i>

17
00:00:50,216 --> 00:00:53,511
But it was too obviously a dentist's toy,
so I was a bit embarrassed.

18
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:56,681
Well, he can't have known
they'd do this after the job reveal.

19
00:00:56,765 --> 00:00:58,892
<i>Oh, they're going in order.</i>

20
00:00:58,975 --> 00:01:01,519
<i>Right. They might not get</i>
<i>to pick the one they want.</i>

21
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:03,354
You're number one, so you go first.

22
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:05,065
NUMBER ONE, SEO-YOON

23
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:07,734
This is hard.

24
00:01:08,234 --> 00:01:10,028
-Take your time.
-No need to rush.

25
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,782
<i>I wanted to go on a date with Seo-yoon.</i>

26
00:01:14,324 --> 00:01:18,328
But since we had
already revealed our jobs,

27
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:21,247
I felt it was really obvious
which one was mine.

28
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:24,250
My item was a mouse.

29
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:26,836
<i>-He's right.</i>
<i>-That's too obvious.</i>

30
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:27,754
<i>It is.</i>

31
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:31,049
<i>I use the mouse all day long…</i>

32
00:01:31,132 --> 00:01:33,009
-Gosh.
-Look at him.

33
00:01:33,092 --> 00:01:35,261
<i>I'm always working or playing games,</i>

34
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:37,514
<i>which has held me back from dating.</i>

35
00:01:38,097 --> 00:01:41,768
My friends jokingly say
my mouse is my girlfriend

36
00:01:41,851 --> 00:01:43,937
<i>because it's always holding my right hand.</i>

37
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:45,814
<i>Since they say that a lot,</i>

38
00:01:45,897 --> 00:01:49,526
it made me think
that's one of the reasons I can't date.

39
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,988
-Why do you two…
-It's…

40
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:56,616
He said it's always
holding his right hand.

41
00:01:56,699 --> 00:01:59,119
I've never thought
of a mouse like that before.

42
00:01:59,744 --> 00:02:01,830
That sigh couldn't have been more genuine.

43
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:10,547
<i>My top pick for today is Jung-yun.</i>

44
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:13,675
<i>I think my second pick is Hyuk-joon.</i>

45
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:17,762
<i>Poor Jae-seo secretly has his hopes up,</i>

46
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:20,473
<i>and the mouse is clearly his.</i>

47
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:22,475
Well…

48
00:02:23,268 --> 00:02:25,895
Since I also brought a book…

49
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,605
I'll pick the book.

50
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:30,024
SEO-YOON PICKS THE BOOK

51
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:32,610
I'm so curious whose it is.

52
00:02:32,694 --> 00:02:34,320
I want to borrow it if I can.

53
00:02:34,404 --> 00:02:37,031
-Oh, so that's why?
-Yeah, I want to borrow it.

54
00:02:37,615 --> 00:02:38,950
-Next.
-Who's next?

55
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:40,785
NUMBER TWO, HAN-JU

56
00:02:40,869 --> 00:02:44,122
<i>Today, I was hoping to go on a date</i>

57
00:02:44,205 --> 00:02:47,876
<i>with either Hyuk-joon or Jin-woo</i>
<i>and have a chance to talk.</i>

58
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:51,963
<i>But I wasn't sure</i>
<i>which item was Hyuk-joon's.</i>

59
00:02:52,714 --> 00:02:55,967
<i>So I picked the item</i>
<i>I was sure was Jin-woo's.</i>

60
00:03:00,513 --> 00:03:01,514
What is that?

61
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:03,516
Isn't that for exercising?

62
00:03:04,058 --> 00:03:05,977
It seems like a tough guy item.
That's why I picked it.

63
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:11,399
Han-ju's figured it out.

64
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:15,570
NUMBER THREE, HYUN-SEO

65
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:19,365
<i>In my case, just by pure chance,</i>

66
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:23,328
<i>I kept getting matched</i>
<i>with Hyuk-joon yesterday.</i>

67
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:26,706
<i>Since I've already gone</i>
<i>on two dates with him,</i>

68
00:03:27,248 --> 00:03:29,709
<i>I wanted to talk with some of the others.</i>

69
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:31,502
<i>-Naturally.</i>
<i>-That's fair.</i>

70
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:32,962
<i>It makes sense to be curious.</i>

71
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:37,216
-I'm so curious about those scissors.
-Me too.

72
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,970
<i>I had no idea</i>
<i>who the scissors belonged to.</i>

73
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:43,556
<i>Since I felt completely clueless,</i>

74
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,975
<i>I thought the owner must be</i>
<i>someone I hadn't talked to.</i>

75
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:48,811
I'm going for the scissors
because I'm so curious.

76
00:03:54,025 --> 00:03:55,944
<i>-The scissors are the biggest mystery.</i>
<i>-Right?</i>

77
00:03:56,027 --> 00:04:01,199
HYUN-SEO PICKS THE SCISSORS

78
00:04:01,282 --> 00:04:04,327
NUMBER FOUR, SU-JI

79
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:08,206
<i>I hoped Su-ji would pick my item.</i>

80
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:10,500
<i>I was</i>

81
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:14,212
<i>hoping to be matched with Su-ji.</i>

82
00:04:15,338 --> 00:04:18,508
<i>I wanted Su-ji to pick mine.</i>

83
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:20,927
All three men have their eye on Su-ji.

84
00:04:21,010 --> 00:04:21,970
She's our Ms. Popular.

85
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,721
I pick this.

86
00:04:25,556 --> 00:04:28,309
<i>I wanted to pick</i>
<i>the metronome from the start.</i>

87
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:30,687
<i>I thought the only guy</i>
<i>who can play an instrument</i>…

88
00:04:30,770 --> 00:04:32,397
SU-JI PICKS THE METRONOME

89
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,482
<i>…was Jung-yun, obviously.</i>

90
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:37,610
<i>-He's happy.</i>
<i>-I think she guessed right.</i>

91
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:41,030
NUMBER FIVE, SOO-HYUN

92
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:42,031
I'll pick…

93
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:46,869
<i>I really wanted to go</i>
<i>on a date with Jin-woo today.</i>

94
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:49,497
<i>But my turn was close to last.</i>

95
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:51,416
I pick the mouse.

96
00:04:53,626 --> 00:04:55,670
<i>I chose the mouse.</i>

97
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:59,132
<i>I guessed it was Jae-seo's.</i>

98
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:01,509
But I thought it could be a toss-up

99
00:05:01,592 --> 00:05:03,344
<i>since Jin-woo majors in architecture</i>

100
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:07,432
<i>and probably would use a mouse</i>
<i>when working on CAD.</i>

101
00:05:07,515 --> 00:05:09,767
She was hoping it would be Jin-woo's.

102
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:10,935
NUMBER SIX, JEONG-EUN

103
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:13,104
-Then, I pick…
-By default.

104
00:05:13,896 --> 00:05:15,064
JEONG-EUN PICKS THE PLUSH TOY

105
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:16,733
-This is too…
-Oh, I had no idea.

106
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:19,152
-It's so obvious.
-What is it? Oh…

107
00:05:20,111 --> 00:05:22,864
<i>They're confused</i>
<i>about the book and the scissors, right?</i>

108
00:05:22,947 --> 00:05:23,781
<i>That's right.</i>

109
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:26,576
Do we say which item is whose now?

110
00:05:26,659 --> 00:05:28,453
Whose book is this?

111
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,126
It's mine.

112
00:05:37,295 --> 00:05:38,713
-It's Jung-yun's?
-What?

113
00:05:38,796 --> 00:05:40,340
That worked out well.

114
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,425
Jung-yun is Seo-yoon's top pick.

115
00:05:42,508 --> 00:05:45,303
-I'm so shocked right now.
-Me too.

116
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:46,679
What about the metronome?

117
00:05:46,763 --> 00:05:47,972
Then who's the metronome owner?

118
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:52,852
<i>I got the chance to go</i>
<i>on a date with Jung-yun,</i>

119
00:05:52,935 --> 00:05:55,063
<i>so I was really happy.</i>

120
00:05:57,607 --> 00:06:01,611
The title was something to do with love.

121
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:03,654
It was such
an eternal single thing to read.

122
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:05,323
So I kept wondering,

123
00:06:05,406 --> 00:06:07,867
"Whose book could that be?"

124
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:09,202
"Why would someone bring it?"

125
00:06:09,285 --> 00:06:12,163
I had no clue whose book it could be.

126
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:16,459
<i>So when he raised his hand</i>
<i>and said it was his…</i>

127
00:06:16,542 --> 00:06:18,753
<i>Her plan has gone completely sideways.</i>

128
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:20,046
<i>Once again.</i>

129
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:21,214
<i>Why again?</i>

130
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:25,510
You guys have gone
on a lot of dates already.

131
00:06:25,593 --> 00:06:26,886
Let me get a turn.

132
00:06:28,304 --> 00:06:29,806
Can I borrow this?

133
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:31,641
Of course.

134
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,728
<i>She showed interest in borrowing the book,</i>

135
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:39,398
so I figured she really wanted to read it.

136
00:06:39,899 --> 00:06:41,901
-That's not it, Jae-seo.
-No, that's not it.

137
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:43,694
Think whatever you like, Jae-seo.

138
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:46,489
-It's better that way.
-You're right.

139
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:48,783
That kind of thinking
gives you peace of mind.

140
00:06:48,866 --> 00:06:49,826
-He's better off.
-He is.

141
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:51,202
-It's less stressful.
-It's better.

142
00:06:51,285 --> 00:06:52,120
-You're right.
-It's true.

143
00:06:52,703 --> 00:06:53,663
Whose is this?

144
00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:54,664
The metronome is mine.

145
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,793
Huh? How is it his?

146
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:00,753
I failed.

147
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:02,839
My calculations were wrong.

148
00:07:03,339 --> 00:07:04,298
Success.

149
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:06,175
I was happy.

150
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:09,220
-Does Tae-hoon also play an instrument?
-Why a metronome?

151
00:07:09,303 --> 00:07:13,391
A metronome keeps a fixed beat.

152
00:07:13,474 --> 00:07:15,268
<i>My daily life</i>

153
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:17,478
<i>and my daily schedule</i>

154
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:20,231
<i>follow a set routine,</i>

155
00:07:20,314 --> 00:07:23,860
so it could be hard to make room
for someone else.

156
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:24,861
That's why

157
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:27,113
I chose a metronome.

158
00:07:28,364 --> 00:07:30,158
That's very symbolic.

159
00:07:30,241 --> 00:07:32,452
It just had to be an item
that could be mistaken for Jung-yun's.

160
00:07:32,535 --> 00:07:34,579
Right? It was too misleading.

161
00:07:34,662 --> 00:07:35,872
He really is a game changer.

162
00:07:36,497 --> 00:07:39,292
But it's a good thing
since Tae-hoon wanted a date with Su-ji.

163
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:41,544
-That's true.
-It worked out well for him.

164
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:44,255
Who does this belong to?

165
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:47,425
That's mine.

166
00:07:50,386 --> 00:07:51,387
-Again?
-These two…

167
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:52,513
She tried to avoid it,

168
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:53,639
-but it's Hyuk-joon again.
-Again?

169
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:55,475
<i>I genuinely got chills.</i>

170
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:57,393
It's just crazy.

171
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:59,103
It made me think

172
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:01,898
that the universe was pushing us together

173
00:08:01,981 --> 00:08:03,483
like fate.

174
00:08:03,983 --> 00:08:06,319
It was kind of scary.

175
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:08,571
We got matched again.

176
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,532
I was amazed.

177
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:12,617
The metronome is mine.

178
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:15,244
Whose mouse is it then?

179
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:16,662
I see.

180
00:08:17,246 --> 00:08:21,083
<i>I already felt comfortable with Soo-hyun.</i>

181
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:23,085
So it wasn't bad at all.

182
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:26,088
<i>I was a little disappointed.</i>

183
00:08:26,672 --> 00:08:29,842
But I decided to use this chance
to find out for certain

184
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:31,677
if it was attraction or friendship.

185
00:08:31,761 --> 00:08:33,179
I wanted to feel it out, so…

186
00:08:34,096 --> 00:08:36,098
I thought it would be
good for us to have a talk.

187
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:38,601
-And this one?
-Whose is this?

188
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:41,437
-Whose is this?
-It's mine.

189
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:43,731
And it <i>is</i> for exercising.

190
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,192
<i>She knew it was his.</i>

191
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:49,403
<i>I guessed right today.</i>

192
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:52,740
<i>I figured it was obvious to everyone</i>

193
00:08:52,823 --> 00:08:56,202
<i>that the wrist strap belonged to Jin-woo.</i>

194
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:58,371
<i>So I was a bit embarrassed.</i>

195
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:01,499
<i>But today, I really wanted to talk</i>

196
00:09:01,582 --> 00:09:04,502
with someone I'm interested in,
so I plucked up my courage.

197
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:07,922
I was most curious to know

198
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:10,967
<i>if she knew it belonged to me</i>
<i>when she picked it.</i>

199
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:12,677
<i>I was really curious.</i>

200
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:15,846
<i>Things seem to finally be going</i>
<i>Han-ju's way.</i>

201
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,348
<i>Goodness.</i>

202
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:18,975
And this?

203
00:09:19,058 --> 00:09:19,892
It's mine.

204
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:28,985
<i>I was a little disappointed</i>
<i>that Hyuk-joon wasn't my date.</i>

205
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:33,906
I have to quickly find
some other way to talk to him.

206
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:37,827
<i>Other than the 15-minute dates,</i>
<i>it's their first proper one-on-one date.</i>

207
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:39,787
<i>Yes, the first real one-on-one dates.</i>

208
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:41,747
-Do we take the items back?
-You should, right?

209
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:43,833
-No, I'm going to use this.
-Oh, you are?

210
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:45,251
It's a gift.

211
00:09:45,793 --> 00:09:47,336
-Do you need to give it back?
-Do we?

212
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:48,254
I don't know.

213
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:49,880
-Shall we take it for now?
-Do we keep it?

214
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,966
-For me to take it…
-It's scary.

215
00:09:52,049 --> 00:09:53,801
-Keep it.
-Really?

216
00:09:53,884 --> 00:09:55,845
-It's quite pricey.
-Yay!

217
00:09:55,928 --> 00:09:57,054
-It's as good as new.
-I mean…

218
00:09:57,138 --> 00:09:59,390
-It's basically new?
-Yeah, I think I used it once.

219
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:03,269
-Awesome.
-It's at least 150,000 won.

220
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:05,521
-I'll see you later.
-See you.

221
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:08,065
-See you later.
-See you in a bit.

222
00:10:09,358 --> 00:10:10,693
KIM JAE-SEO
CHOI HYUK-JOON

223
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:11,902
It must be fate.

224
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:13,404
Seriously. Is this a sign?

225
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:16,866
-It's been happening since yesterday.
-Exactly.

226
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:18,993
-Do you click well?
-We do.

227
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:22,955
-It's like… It's weird.
-Yeah.

228
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:25,583
-I've got goosebumps.
-How is this possible?

229
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:28,544
-And your item was really random.
-Right.

230
00:10:29,837 --> 00:10:30,880
It must be fate…

231
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:34,800
I do kind of believe in fate.

232
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:37,428
But this is so crazy.

233
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:42,433
You just got here,
and you're going on a one-on-one date.

234
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:43,476
I know.

235
00:10:44,226 --> 00:10:46,854
It's everyone's
first actual one-on-one date.

236
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:49,315
-I'm so excited!
-This is so great.

237
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:50,232
I'm hyped.

238
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:52,193
How is every day so exciting?

239
00:10:52,276 --> 00:10:53,110
I love it.

240
00:10:53,194 --> 00:10:54,987
I was so nervous yesterday
that I couldn't eat much.

241
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:56,447
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT YOUR FIRST ONE-ON-ONE DATE?

242
00:10:57,239 --> 00:11:00,117
I decided to just enjoy it.

243
00:11:00,701 --> 00:11:03,204
What if I get
an upset stomach from nerves?

244
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:05,039
Are you nervous?

245
00:11:05,122 --> 00:11:07,541
Yeah, it's the first time
going out one-on-one.

246
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:10,795
This one?

247
00:11:11,379 --> 00:11:13,464
Hey, that's not bad! You look good.

248
00:11:13,547 --> 00:11:15,549
What about this one?

249
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:17,259
I think that's better.

250
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:21,055
<i>I was a bit nervous.</i>

251
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:24,058
<i>I'm going to try to flirt.</i>

252
00:11:24,141 --> 00:11:25,810
-Yes, try it.
-You can do it.

253
00:11:26,394 --> 00:11:27,353
<i>It's Tae-hoon and Su-ji.</i>

254
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:28,938
It's a curry place.

255
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:29,980
Do you like curry?

256
00:11:30,064 --> 00:11:31,524
Curry? Yeah, I do.

257
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:32,441
You do?

258
00:11:33,401 --> 00:11:35,528
-Should we get two regular curries?
-Yes.

259
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:37,113
I want it mildly spicy.

260
00:11:37,613 --> 00:11:39,907
-I'll go for the same one.
-Okay.

261
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:42,326
<i>I joined yesterday as a game changer…</i>

262
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:45,162
I feel like five sisters-in-law
are interviewing me.

263
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,414
What are you talking about?

264
00:11:46,497 --> 00:11:49,208
<i>I was too awkward</i>
<i>and didn't leave a good impression.</i>

265
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:51,919
<i>I want to make up for that screw-up today.</i>

266
00:11:52,002 --> 00:11:54,296
Yes. You have to make up
for that, Tae-hoon.

267
00:11:55,464 --> 00:11:57,007
<i>To be honest,</i>

268
00:11:57,091 --> 00:12:01,053
I wasn't really interested in Tae-hoon.

269
00:12:01,137 --> 00:12:03,556
But I was curious to see

270
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:06,851
if going on a date with him
might change my feelings.

271
00:12:06,934 --> 00:12:08,644
<i>So I thought it worked out for the better.</i>

272
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:11,897
Who did you pick for the 5 Minute Library?

273
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:13,858
-Today?
-Wait. Can I guess?

274
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:15,818
I bet…

275
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:18,737
you read Hyun-seo's diary.

276
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:21,532
-Am I right?
-No.

277
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:23,159
-Whose, then?
-Well…

278
00:12:23,784 --> 00:12:25,744
-I read yours today.
-Oh, really?

279
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:27,872
-Oh, really?
-Yes.

280
00:12:27,955 --> 00:12:30,249
It finally feels like a dating show.

281
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:31,375
Why did you pick mine?

282
00:12:32,668 --> 00:12:34,879
-Yesterday, we talked…
-Yeah?

283
00:12:34,962 --> 00:12:36,213
We talked more than the others.

284
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:38,424
-We did.
-Since we were sitting side-by-side.

285
00:12:38,507 --> 00:12:40,050
-We were.
-So I got curious.

286
00:12:44,346 --> 00:12:45,431
This is so exciting.

287
00:12:45,514 --> 00:12:49,518
Tae-hoon gets quite soft
when he's with someone he likes.

288
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:50,561
-He does.
-Yeah.

289
00:12:50,644 --> 00:12:52,771
He's being gentle. It's nice to see.

290
00:12:53,355 --> 00:12:56,275
<i>I was honest about the fact</i>
<i>that I read Su-ji's diary today</i>

291
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:58,486
<i>in the 5 Minute Library.</i>

292
00:12:59,487 --> 00:13:02,364
But talking to her after reading her diary

293
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:03,741
was a double-edged sword.

294
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:05,576
-What?
-What does he mean by that?

295
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,037
It kind of worked against me

296
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:10,247
<i>because I already knew some stuff,</i>

297
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:13,125
so I had fewer questions to ask.

298
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:16,629
<i>That made it harder</i>
<i>to keep the conversation flowing.</i>

299
00:13:22,384 --> 00:13:24,220
Don't you have any questions for me?

300
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:27,598
Did you find out too much
in the 5 Minute Library?

301
00:13:27,681 --> 00:13:29,350
-I think I read too much.
-Why did you?

302
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:32,353
You should have asked me in person.

303
00:13:32,436 --> 00:13:34,188
Why did you have to pick the metronome?

304
00:13:34,271 --> 00:13:35,397
-What?
-Come on!

305
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:38,150
Okay. You… All right.

306
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:40,236
That's how you're going to play it? Okay.

307
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:42,238
-This is…
-Okay, Tae-hoon.

308
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:43,614
Curry is where it ends for you.

309
00:13:43,697 --> 00:13:44,698
You know escape rooms?

310
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:47,701
He went into one,
then turned around and left.

311
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:48,786
-Why did he do that?
-Oh, dear.

312
00:13:48,869 --> 00:13:50,454
-It was going so well.
-This is…

313
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:51,497
That's one way to escape.

314
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:54,208
Don't girls hate hearing
something like that?

315
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:56,335
It's the kind of joke
you don't know how to respond to.

316
00:13:56,418 --> 00:13:57,962
-It's the worst.
-Right? What can you say?

317
00:13:58,045 --> 00:13:58,879
Okay.

318
00:14:01,006 --> 00:14:04,468
I'm not used to small talk with women.

319
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:07,221
-For me, talking to guys…
-I can tell.

320
00:14:07,304 --> 00:14:08,222
It's more fun.

321
00:14:08,847 --> 00:14:11,058
-Are you not having fun now?
-No, I don't mean that.

322
00:14:11,141 --> 00:14:12,226
-I mean in general.
-Right.

323
00:14:12,309 --> 00:14:14,687
Tae-hoon has a serious problem.

324
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:18,649
Do you like any weird food?

325
00:14:18,732 --> 00:14:19,608
Weird food?

326
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:20,901
Mine's written in my diary.

327
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:23,737
Weird food…

328
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:32,663
<i>She asked me a question,</i>

329
00:14:32,746 --> 00:14:35,207
but my memory was fuzzy,

330
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:36,625
<i>so I was a bit flustered.</i>

331
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:39,628
So what was that nonsense
about a double-edged sword?

332
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:41,630
He doesn't even remember.

333
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:44,425
Bring up something you do remember.

334
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:46,552
-I don't remember.
-You don't, do you?

335
00:14:46,635 --> 00:14:48,137
-It's hard to recall, isn't it?
-Yeah.

336
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:49,054
In that case…

337
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:51,140
Was there a question

338
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:53,309
that was memorable?

339
00:14:53,392 --> 00:14:55,185
-I mean, my answer to it.
-Your answer?

340
00:14:55,269 --> 00:14:57,146
Did you find any of my answers memorable?

341
00:14:58,147 --> 00:14:58,981
Any thoughts?

342
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,945
-You don't remember, do you?
-No.

343
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:05,946
I was in a rush.

344
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:08,699
-You were too rushed.
-Yes, I was.

345
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:11,452
<i>Because I was so short on time,</i>

346
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:14,872
I wasn't able to fully memorize
her answers, so…

347
00:15:15,789 --> 00:15:16,749
That's where I messed up.

348
00:15:16,832 --> 00:15:19,001
-I mean…
-Just say something.

349
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:22,046
I guess you have a bad memory.

350
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,799
At least he's quick to answer.

351
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:27,259
Is it spicy for you? You're sweating.

352
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:29,386
Do you need a tissue?

353
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:31,972
-It must be too spicy.
-No, I…

354
00:15:32,056 --> 00:15:33,515
-Why pick this spice level
-It's not that…

355
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:34,934
-and not something milder?
-No, I…

356
00:15:35,017 --> 00:15:35,976
It's not that spicy.

357
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:40,606
This level of spice is usually fine.

358
00:15:40,689 --> 00:15:42,316
I didn't think I'd sweat like this.

359
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:46,695
<i>That level of spice doesn't</i>
<i>usually make me sweat.</i>

360
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:50,366
But maybe my nervous system
was in overdrive.

361
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:53,744
I reacted more sensitively than usual
and sweated buckets.

362
00:15:53,827 --> 00:15:55,913
I sweated because it was spicy,

363
00:15:55,996 --> 00:15:57,915
but I was worried it might seem

364
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:01,085
like I was just really nervous.

365
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:03,754
<i>So when I realized I was sweating,</i>

366
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:05,464
<i>I got anxious.</i>

367
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:09,551
WAS IT A SATISFYING DATE
FOR YOU AS A GAME CHANGER?

368
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:10,469
Well…

369
00:16:10,552 --> 00:16:12,262
I'll do my best to stir things up.

370
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:16,016
Thinking about it too much
is only going to give me a headache.

371
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:19,645
So I decided to just put it behind me.

372
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:21,355
He's basically given up.

373
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:23,273
Will he be the first one ever to drop out?

374
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:26,735
<i>I felt really thrown</i>

375
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:28,320
because my feelings didn't change at all.

376
00:16:28,821 --> 00:16:30,781
So I felt very flustered.

377
00:16:34,034 --> 00:16:35,703
This date is a complete flop.

378
00:16:36,203 --> 00:16:38,080
I feel so bad for them
that I'm speechless.

379
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:40,374
-Right? It's such a shame.
-What can you say, right?

380
00:16:40,457 --> 00:16:42,543
Instead of stirring things up,
he screwed things up.

381
00:16:42,626 --> 00:16:43,585
Right?

382
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:46,964
Tae-hoon is definitely
proving that he's an eternal single.

383
00:16:47,047 --> 00:16:48,674
I think Tae-hoon

384
00:16:48,757 --> 00:16:51,135
needs to say at the start of every date,

385
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:54,096
"I'm not used to small talk with women,

386
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:56,724
I can be quite prickly and blunt,

387
00:16:56,807 --> 00:16:58,559
but that's not how I mean it at all,

388
00:16:58,642 --> 00:17:01,395
and it's just a reflex
when I get nervous or embarrassed,

389
00:17:01,478 --> 00:17:02,896
so don't take it to heart."

390
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:04,940
That's how he should start his dates.

391
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:07,234
Or he could print off a disclaimer.

392
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:09,194
-Hand it out.
-He should carry it around

393
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:10,112
and hand it out.

394
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:11,363
-"Read this before we start."
-A disclaimer!

395
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:13,115
Didn't he call himself a metronome

396
00:17:13,198 --> 00:17:15,367
-because he moves perfectly on beat?
-I know.

397
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:17,036
-He's so offbeat.
-A metronome? Yeah, right.

398
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:18,412
-More like jazz.
-It's such a shame.

399
00:17:18,495 --> 00:17:19,705
What if he said this?

400
00:17:19,788 --> 00:17:21,415
"So why did you have to pick a metronome?"

401
00:17:21,999 --> 00:17:23,042
"You made my heart skip a beat."

402
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:24,835
-That's great!
-I love it.

403
00:17:24,918 --> 00:17:26,462
-That's the stuff.
-What a great line.

404
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:28,589
-He never has any follow-through.
-He doesn't!

405
00:17:28,672 --> 00:17:30,841
Why didn't he do
as Car, the garden taught him?

406
00:17:30,924 --> 00:17:32,551
I didn't know he was that bad!

407
00:17:34,762 --> 00:17:35,763
ONE-ON-ONE DATE
JIN-WOO, HAN-JU

408
00:17:35,846 --> 00:17:36,847
I guess I'll be driving.

409
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:39,391
I'm sorry to put you out, but thank you.

410
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:41,435
-You can trust me.
-Yes, ma'am.

411
00:17:42,394 --> 00:17:44,688
<i>Since I'm interested in Jin-woo,</i>

412
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:47,149
I'm excited to go on a date with him.

413
00:17:48,275 --> 00:17:49,651
Han-ju is driving.

414
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:51,570
Jin-woo doesn't have a license yet.

415
00:17:51,653 --> 00:17:52,905
And that's okay.

416
00:17:53,947 --> 00:17:55,657
I feel a bit nervous about driving.

417
00:17:56,283 --> 00:17:58,243
Don't worry. I'll save you if we crash.

418
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:02,247
Or we can just die together.

419
00:18:04,124 --> 00:18:08,003
-I'm a bit of a fearless driver.
-I like that.

420
00:18:08,629 --> 00:18:10,756
Han-ju is a boss lady.

421
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:15,010
Have you met someone
with the same MBTI as you before?

422
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,011
No, I haven't.

423
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:18,305
-I've hardly ever met another ISTP.
-You haven't? Really?

424
00:18:18,388 --> 00:18:19,890
Did you know ISTPs

425
00:18:19,973 --> 00:18:22,893
-have a bad rep in dating?
-I know.

426
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:24,770
-And for having set preferences.
-That too.

427
00:18:24,853 --> 00:18:28,107
They say that in order to date an ISTP,

428
00:18:28,690 --> 00:18:30,442
you just need to look their type.

429
00:18:30,526 --> 00:18:32,402
Right! That's why…

430
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:34,655
They say we're obsessed with looks.

431
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:36,281
-True.
-And I only care about looks.

432
00:18:38,408 --> 00:18:40,327
-You like good-looking guys?
-Yes.

433
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:46,792
I've already told the girls this, but…

434
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:47,918
Okay.

435
00:18:48,001 --> 00:18:50,921
Just in terms of looks,

436
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:53,507
you're most my type.

437
00:18:55,509 --> 00:18:57,719
-She just threw it out there mid-drive.
-It was so casual.

438
00:18:57,803 --> 00:18:59,263
She said it like it was nothing.

439
00:19:01,056 --> 00:19:02,099
-Me?
-Yes.

440
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:06,270
When I first saw you,
I thought you had a handsome face.

441
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:09,731
Then, when you did the arm-wrestling,

442
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:11,608
I was watching from the back,

443
00:19:11,692 --> 00:19:13,944
and I noticed your lats were huge, so…

444
00:19:14,027 --> 00:19:15,320
That's also important.

445
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:16,405
I'm just saying.

446
00:19:17,781 --> 00:19:19,074
She's so honest.

447
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:20,784
-For a guy who works out,
-Exactly.

448
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:22,536
-it's the highest compliment.
-It is.

449
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:25,164
-Lock the doors so he can't get out.
-She should.

450
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:26,498
<i>He seems to feel shy.</i>

451
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:29,459
<i>I was really taken aback.</i>

452
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:34,673
I didn't think
Han-ju had any interest in me.

453
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:36,466
She didn't show any signs.

454
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:38,135
<i>That's why it was more surprising.</i>

455
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:41,513
I'm curious about everyone's age.

456
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:43,390
I really want to know how old everyone is.

457
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:47,227
Do you think I'm older,
younger, or the same age?

458
00:19:47,311 --> 00:19:48,187
I think you're older.

459
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:49,188
-You think so?
-Yes.

460
00:19:49,271 --> 00:19:52,316
-<i>She's a doctor, after all.</i>
-What's your usual preference?

461
00:19:52,399 --> 00:19:54,109
-Do you mean in terms of age?
-Yes.

462
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:57,446
-Older women?
-Really?

463
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:01,450
-Liar.
-What?

464
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:04,244
-Hey, why are you lying?
-Seriously.

465
00:20:04,328 --> 00:20:05,954
-That wasn't his answer in the diary.
-That's not true.

466
00:20:06,038 --> 00:20:08,999
<i>He ranked same age first,</i>
<i>then someone younger,</i>

467
00:20:09,082 --> 00:20:11,168
<i>and older women were his last choice.</i>

468
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:14,630
-Is this a sign he's into Han-ju?
-Right?

469
00:20:14,713 --> 00:20:17,049
"I think you're older than me,
and I like older women."

470
00:20:17,132 --> 00:20:18,217
That's quite…

471
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,469
But what's funny is

472
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:22,888
we should be praising him,
but we're all like, "What?"

473
00:20:22,971 --> 00:20:24,681
-It's so odd.
-An eternal single

474
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:26,058
made a remark like that?

475
00:20:26,141 --> 00:20:27,059
-He's so smooth.
-He is.

476
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:29,978
-So we're all a little flustered.
-Jin-woo's doing so great.

477
00:20:30,812 --> 00:20:32,105
I think we're here.

478
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:36,693
I'm a good driver, right?

479
00:20:36,777 --> 00:20:39,029
-Totally cool, right?
-You're an excellent driver.

480
00:20:39,112 --> 00:20:41,281
<i>-She's really perked up.</i>
-You seem very sophisticated.

481
00:20:42,741 --> 00:20:43,784
Oh, sorry.

482
00:20:44,826 --> 00:20:46,119
-Boss lady.
-Darn it.

483
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:49,248
-I ruined it at the end.
-That's how tough girls park.

484
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:51,708
Let's get out.

485
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:52,668
Let's go.

486
00:20:56,838 --> 00:20:58,382
Oh, it's a traditional liquor place.

487
00:20:59,299 --> 00:21:00,425
Will we be drinking?

488
00:21:00,509 --> 00:21:01,468
Maybe.

489
00:21:01,551 --> 00:21:03,011
Didn't you say you like to drink?

490
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:04,471
Yes!

491
00:21:05,222 --> 00:21:06,473
