608
00:26:04,729 --> 00:26:07,107
But just like some guys
like being called <i>oppa</i>,

609
00:26:07,190 --> 00:26:10,860
I like to be called<i> nuna</i> by younger guys,

610
00:26:10,944 --> 00:26:12,445
so I told him to call me that.

611
00:26:13,571 --> 00:26:15,991
<i>I was glad to go on a date with Jin-woo</i>

612
00:26:16,074 --> 00:26:18,451
<i>as I wanted to get to know him.</i>

613
00:26:18,535 --> 00:26:20,829
<i>And the date was really fun,</i>

614
00:26:20,912 --> 00:26:23,873
<i>so my current top pick is Jin-woo.</i>

615
00:26:23,957 --> 00:26:24,791
<i>Okay.</i>

616
00:26:24,874 --> 00:26:26,626
<i>That was such an easygoing date.</i>

617
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:27,711
<i>What a relief, Han-ju!</i>

618
00:26:27,794 --> 00:26:30,046
-Today feels like a day to drink.
-Let's go crazy.

619
00:26:30,130 --> 00:26:31,506
-Why, you…
-"Let's go crazy."

620
00:26:32,465 --> 00:26:34,009
-You little…
-"Why, you…"

621
00:26:34,592 --> 00:26:36,052
That caught me so off guard.

622
00:26:36,136 --> 00:26:39,347
This is the most anxious
I've been on this show.

623
00:26:39,431 --> 00:26:40,682
It was like a real date.

624
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:43,226
-It really was.
-It was like a real first date.

625
00:26:43,310 --> 00:26:45,478
Han-ju seems so satisfied.

626
00:26:45,562 --> 00:26:47,105
She seems so happy.

627
00:26:48,106 --> 00:26:50,442
<i>-Hello.</i>
<i>-Hello.</i>

628
00:26:50,525 --> 00:26:52,068
ONE-ON-ONE DATE
JUNG-YUN, SEO-YOON

629
00:26:52,652 --> 00:26:53,945
This is a s'more kit.

630
00:26:54,029 --> 00:26:54,863
-Okay.
-Oh my gosh.

631
00:26:54,946 --> 00:26:56,698
Take a biscuit and toast the marshmallow,

632
00:26:56,781 --> 00:26:58,658
then dip it in the chocolate and enjoy.

633
00:26:58,742 --> 00:26:59,617
Okay.

634
00:27:00,201 --> 00:27:01,619
-Thank you.
-You were craving chocolate.

635
00:27:01,703 --> 00:27:05,332
I was. I needed a sweet pick-me-up.

636
00:27:06,041 --> 00:27:07,959
<i>Don't they look so cute together?</i>

637
00:27:08,043 --> 00:27:09,127
<i>Yesterday,</i>

638
00:27:09,210 --> 00:27:11,546
I spent quite a bit of time with Jung-yun

639
00:27:11,629 --> 00:27:14,049
<i>on our Random Spot Date.</i>

640
00:27:14,132 --> 00:27:16,051
<i>And while we were talking,</i>

641
00:27:16,134 --> 00:27:18,553
<i>I didn't have any desire</i>

642
00:27:18,636 --> 00:27:20,930
<i>to talk with anyone else.</i>

643
00:27:21,014 --> 00:27:23,224
So I decided

644
00:27:23,308 --> 00:27:25,894
that I will be brave today

645
00:27:25,977 --> 00:27:29,314
<i>and give it my best shot.</i>

646
00:27:29,397 --> 00:27:32,275
Seo-yoon's top pick
has been Jung-yun from the get-go.

647
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:33,693
-It's been him from the start.
-It has.

648
00:27:33,777 --> 00:27:34,819
They're kind of cute.

649
00:27:34,903 --> 00:27:37,030
<i>They're so cute,</i>
<i>like teen lovers in an anime.</i>

650
00:27:38,239 --> 00:27:39,783
-Is it a message alert?
-What was that?

651
00:27:41,743 --> 00:27:42,577
A text.

652
00:27:46,289 --> 00:27:49,292
"Reveal your age to your date."

653
00:27:49,876 --> 00:27:51,836
-Oh my word.
-Oh my gosh.

654
00:27:52,462 --> 00:27:53,838
-Oh, goodness.
-I am…

655
00:27:53,922 --> 00:27:54,923
Shall I go first?

656
00:27:55,006 --> 00:27:57,133
No, I think I'm probably much older.

657
00:27:57,217 --> 00:27:58,176
So I'll go first.

658
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:00,595
<i>Seo-yoon's a bit insecure about her age.</i>

659
00:28:00,678 --> 00:28:01,513
I am…

660
00:28:03,056 --> 00:28:04,474
I'm 29 years old.

661
00:28:04,557 --> 00:28:06,434
-Really?
-Yes, I was born in 1997.

662
00:28:07,310 --> 00:28:08,186
What about you?

663
00:28:09,396 --> 00:28:10,438
I'm 26 years old.

664
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:12,482
-Oh, really? Then… 2000?
-I was born in 2000.

665
00:28:13,108 --> 00:28:16,361
Is the 7th digit
of your resident number 3?

666
00:28:16,444 --> 00:28:17,278
Yes.

667
00:28:19,739 --> 00:28:20,865
Is it that funny?

668
00:28:24,744 --> 00:28:26,538
Was <i>Pop-up Pirate</i> two days ago?
Were you there?

669
00:28:26,621 --> 00:28:27,539
-I was.
-Didn't you

670
00:28:27,622 --> 00:28:29,958
-ask that question then?
-What question?

671
00:28:30,041 --> 00:28:31,793
If we prefer the same age,
younger, or older…

672
00:28:31,876 --> 00:28:34,337
-Oh, right. I asked that.
-You did.

673
00:28:34,963 --> 00:28:35,797
I said younger.

674
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,298
Because for me…

675
00:28:37,966 --> 00:28:39,050
Right.

676
00:28:39,634 --> 00:28:41,845
-The reason I said I prefer younger guys…
-Yes.

677
00:28:42,429 --> 00:28:43,972
When I was in my early twenties…

678
00:28:44,055 --> 00:28:47,851
Well, for a really long time,
I've been a fangirl of a K-pop idol group.

679
00:28:47,934 --> 00:28:49,436
Can I ask which group?

680
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:53,273
-It's NCT DREAM.
-DREAM?

681
00:28:53,356 --> 00:28:54,274
