-I mean…

692
00:29:23,428 --> 00:29:25,805
For example,
the trot singer, Lim Young-woong…

693
00:29:25,889 --> 00:29:28,224
-That's so random.
-He's talking nonsense.

694
00:29:28,850 --> 00:29:31,770
People think that only older people

695
00:29:31,853 --> 00:29:34,022
are into trot music and stuff.

696
00:29:34,105 --> 00:29:36,107
But anyone can…

697
00:29:37,108 --> 00:29:38,777
I mean…

698
00:29:38,860 --> 00:29:42,697
-Anyone can be into singers and actors.
-You think so?

699
00:29:43,907 --> 00:29:47,368
Jung-yun said he understood

700
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:50,830
older people going fanatic
over trot singers.

701
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:53,708
But when he said that,

702
00:29:54,292 --> 00:29:58,213
it made me wonder if he was
trying to say that I was old.

703
00:29:59,547 --> 00:30:02,884
That thought kind of crossed my mind.

704
00:30:02,967 --> 00:30:04,844
-That's not it.
-He didn't mean that.

705
00:30:04,928 --> 00:30:07,222
What Jung-yun meant was this.

706
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:10,725
-Fandom is a sort of community.
-It's no big deal.

707
00:30:10,809 --> 00:30:12,560
-Age doesn't matter.
-He gets it.

708
00:30:12,644 --> 00:30:15,438
He was trying to say
that it's good to be someone's fan.

709
00:30:15,522 --> 00:30:18,191
But because he suddenly
brought up a trot singer,

710
00:30:18,274 --> 00:30:20,318
she's wondering if he thinks she's old.

711
00:30:20,401 --> 00:30:22,070
-Right.
-It's possible she misunderstood.

712
00:30:22,153 --> 00:30:24,197
She's only a year away from 30,
so she's got a lot on her mind.

713
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:25,156
Just a year away.

714
00:30:29,077 --> 00:30:31,621
To be completely honest…

715
00:30:33,873 --> 00:30:35,667
during the first impression vote…

716
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:37,210
-Yeah?
-I chose you.

717
00:30:37,919 --> 00:30:39,504
Really? I had no idea.

718
00:30:40,672 --> 00:30:42,340
But I'm curious to know…

719
00:30:42,423 --> 00:30:44,968
How did you feel about our chat yesterday?

720
00:30:45,051 --> 00:30:45,927
Our chat?

721
00:30:51,099 --> 00:30:52,267
It was good…

722
00:30:53,268 --> 00:30:55,728
I felt it flowed well.

723
00:30:55,812 --> 00:30:57,522
It flowed well and…

724
00:30:57,605 --> 00:31:00,650
-I felt we have similar hobbies and stuff.
-Right.

725
00:31:00,733 --> 00:31:02,402
That was my takeaway.

726
00:31:05,113 --> 00:31:07,407
But at the end of the day…

727
00:31:07,490 --> 00:31:09,409
<i>Oh, where is this going?</i>

728
00:31:10,368 --> 00:31:13,121
It's still early days,
and there are six women.

729
00:31:13,204 --> 00:31:16,958
-Right.
-So I want to talk with everyone.

730
00:31:17,041 --> 00:31:19,502
But there are people
I wanted to talk to more.

731
00:31:20,336 --> 00:31:21,170
And…

732
00:31:23,214 --> 00:31:25,884
-Did I already say this?
-What?

733
00:31:25,967 --> 00:31:28,344
-When we did the towel game…
-Yes?

734
00:31:28,428 --> 00:31:29,387
The towel…

735
00:31:30,763 --> 00:31:33,474
-You mean when Su-ji gave it to you?
-Yes.

736
00:31:33,558 --> 00:31:34,684
So, I…

