a bit different once they dry.

766
00:33:10,613 --> 00:33:11,656
-She's an expert.
-Art major.

767
00:33:11,739 --> 00:33:13,992
They can get lighter or darker.

768
00:33:15,827 --> 00:33:17,870
It's a bit different. It's kind of brown…

769
00:33:22,583 --> 00:33:26,004
-I envy people who do art or music.
-Why?

770
00:33:26,629 --> 00:33:29,549
Having knowledge
in boring subjects like sciences…

771
00:33:30,466 --> 00:33:33,386
You can enjoy them on your own.

772
00:33:34,012 --> 00:33:37,640
But you can't use them
to do anything for your friends.

773
00:33:39,142 --> 00:33:41,102
Whereas with things like art and music,

774
00:33:41,185 --> 00:33:44,397
-if you can sing, you can go to<i> noraebang.</i>
-Sing together.

775
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:48,234
You can share your talent
with others and enjoy it together.

776
00:33:48,317 --> 00:33:49,694
-Right.
-That's an advantage.

777
00:33:49,777 --> 00:33:51,738
You don't recite the times tables
with friends, do you?

778
00:33:51,821 --> 00:33:52,822
-That's true.
-Right?

779
00:33:53,990 --> 00:33:56,367
-You know what you're talking about.
-<i>It's a nice chat.</i>

780
00:33:56,451 --> 00:33:58,911
I'm not good at art,
but I have a lot of interest in it.

781
00:33:59,537 --> 00:34:01,956
Even in gaming, there are trending colors.

782
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:04,000
Depending on the era…

783
00:34:04,083 --> 00:34:07,086
It's hard to explain,
but right now, it's purple.

784
00:34:07,170 --> 00:34:09,422
The most famous game uses a lot of purple.

785
00:34:10,006 --> 00:34:13,259
But that's recently changed
to yellow and gold.

786
00:34:13,342 --> 00:34:14,302
-Right.
-But…

787
00:34:20,808 --> 00:34:23,436
<i>If a game uses too much bright red,</i>
<i>it can hurt your eyes.</i>

788
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:28,566
So you need to consider
the impact of the colors in the game.

789
00:34:28,649 --> 00:34:30,443
Is this a YouTube tutorial or what?

790
00:34:31,444 --> 00:34:34,363
Why the sudden lecture?

791
00:34:34,447 --> 00:34:36,532
Jae-seo's in his element.

792
00:34:36,616 --> 00:34:38,159
They use more realistic colors.

793
00:34:38,785 --> 00:34:39,660
Maybe we were too loud.

794
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:41,245
-Did you have fun?
<i>-Yes, let's stop here.</i>

795
00:34:41,329 --> 00:34:42,747
<i>-Okay.</i>
<i>-Good timing.</i>

796
00:34:42,830 --> 00:34:44,665
-I have a question.
-Sure.

797
00:34:44,749 --> 00:34:46,084
You know things like…

798
00:34:46,167 --> 00:34:47,293
What was it? Primary colors?

799
00:34:47,376 --> 00:34:48,920
Colors like red and green.

800
00:34:49,003 --> 00:34:52,465
I feel like pure colors like that

801
00:34:52,548 --> 00:34:54,842
might actually be harder to find.

802
00:34:54,926 --> 00:34:57,887
I didn't recognize
any of the colors on this.

803
00:34:57,970 --> 00:35:01,557
So I was wondering if pure colors
are actually hard to find in nature…

804
00:35:01,641 --> 00:35:03,101
-What I mean is…
-Yes?

805
00:35:03,184 --> 00:35:06,854
Is ultramarine really a pure color?

806
00:35:07,605 --> 00:35:10,149
I think the conversation went well.

807
00:35:10,233 --> 00:35:11,609
I had so much fun.

808
00:35:11,692 --> 00:35:14,028
Unbelievable.

809
00:35:14,112 --> 00:35:16,405
-I can't even…
-It needs to go both ways.

810
00:35:16,489 --> 00:35:17,406
He pat himself on the back

811
00:35:17,490 --> 00:35:19,325
-He just kept rambling.
-for talking nonsense.

812
00:35:19,909 --> 00:35:21,369
Oh, dear.

813
00:35:23,371 --> 00:35:25,706
He spoke with a lot of passion,

814
00:35:25,790 --> 00:35:28,417
but his answer felt quite long.

815
00:35:28,501 --> 00:35:31,546
He explained things in detail,

816
00:35:31,629 --> 00:35:35,758
and it kind of got a bit drawn out.

817
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:38,845
Jae-seo needs to know
how to dial it down a bit.

818
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:40,429
It looks so tasty.

819
00:35:40,513 --> 00:35:42,140
-Enjoy.
-You too.

820
00:35:44,183 --> 00:35:45,143
This is so good.

821
00:35:45,226 --> 00:35:46,394
It is.

