because you've already wound it, no?

954
00:40:45,025 --> 00:40:46,777
One, two, three.

955
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:47,736
Wait a minute.

956
00:40:49,530 --> 00:40:51,365
Why do I feel like this isn't working?

957
00:40:52,074 --> 00:40:53,200
He's a bit frustrating.

958
00:40:53,951 --> 00:40:55,661
One, two, three.

959
00:40:55,744 --> 00:40:56,620
Wait.

960
00:40:57,371 --> 00:40:58,581
Did you take it?

961
00:40:58,664 --> 00:41:00,332
Sorry.

962
00:41:00,416 --> 00:41:01,375
-It's working now!
-Did it work?

963
00:41:01,459 --> 00:41:02,877
-I swear this is the last time.
-Okay.

964
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:03,878
I'm sorry.

965
00:41:04,712 --> 00:41:07,631
<i>The date itself was really fun,</i>

966
00:41:07,715 --> 00:41:10,384
but after this date,
I started to see Seung-hyun

967
00:41:10,468 --> 00:41:13,596
as just a really good friend.

968
00:41:13,679 --> 00:41:16,223
I really don't have

969
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:18,559
any romantic feelings for him at all.

970
00:41:18,642 --> 00:41:20,644
Yeah, that's fair.

971
00:41:20,728 --> 00:41:22,354
I love how quickly
they make their verdict.

972
00:41:22,438 --> 00:41:25,357
Eternal singles are so quick
to reach a decision.

973
00:41:25,441 --> 00:41:26,901
-They're very fast.
-It's quick.

974
00:41:27,485 --> 00:41:29,570
DID THE DATE GO WELL?

975
00:41:29,653 --> 00:41:32,781
Blunders…
I don't think I made any blunders.

976
00:41:32,865 --> 00:41:33,908
I'm not really… Well…

977
00:41:35,784 --> 00:41:37,870
I'm not, well, really sure.

978
00:41:37,953 --> 00:41:39,038
I thought it went fine.

979
00:41:40,039 --> 00:41:42,249
-Fine, think whatever you like.
-Jeez.

980
00:41:42,333 --> 00:41:45,169
I think Seung-hyun was too nervous.

981
00:41:45,252 --> 00:41:48,881
But Seung-hyun might have fallen for her.

982
00:41:48,964 --> 00:41:50,883
-For Jeong-eun?
-He falls in love easily.

983
00:41:50,966 --> 00:41:53,135
-He's easily swayed.
-He is.

984
00:41:53,219 --> 00:41:54,970
He might have been taken by her beauty

985
00:41:55,054 --> 00:41:56,305
while taking her photo.

986
00:41:56,388 --> 00:41:58,807
-After a date with Seung-hyun…
-The women don't feel a spark.

987
00:41:58,891 --> 00:42:00,518
They all felt he's not a match.

988
00:42:00,601 --> 00:42:02,353
It's not easy being an eternal single.

989
00:42:02,978 --> 00:42:03,812
ONE-ON-ONE DATE
HYUK-JOON, HYUN-SEO

990
00:42:03,896 --> 00:42:04,772
<i>I'm curious about them.</i>

991
00:42:04,855 --> 00:42:07,066
<i>-This one's a must-see.</i>
<i>-I wanted to see this one the most.</i>

992
00:42:07,816 --> 00:42:08,859
<i>They're going kayaking?</i>

993
00:42:08,943 --> 00:42:10,819
<i>Looks like Hyun-seo is into activities.</i>

994
00:42:10,903 --> 00:42:11,779
<i>Put on the life vests.</i>

995
00:42:13,781 --> 00:42:15,616
-Dress me.
-Yes, ma'am.

996
00:42:15,699 --> 00:42:16,700
She said, "Dress me."

997
00:42:16,784 --> 00:42:19,411
Hyun-seo sometimes talks
like an anime character.

998
00:42:21,121 --> 00:42:23,207
I think you use this to tighten it.

999
00:42:24,291 --> 00:42:25,125
This?

1000
00:42:30,548 --> 00:42:33,050
This is a rare sight on our show.

1001
00:42:37,137 --> 00:42:38,931
<i>In his diary, he said he gets butterflies</i>

1002
00:42:39,014 --> 00:42:42,268
<i>when a girl picks lint off his shirt,</i>

1003
00:42:42,351 --> 00:42:46,063
<i>and he wore a sweater on the date,</i>
<i>but it had no pilling at all, so…</i>

1004
00:42:46,814 --> 00:42:48,524
I realized it won't be so easy.

1005
00:42:51,193 --> 00:42:52,319
There's a bug.

1006
00:42:55,489 --> 00:42:56,323
-She's good.
-Well done.

1007
00:42:56,407 --> 00:42:57,533
Well done, Hyun-seo.

1008
00:42:58,534 --> 00:43:01,161
<i>He seemed pretty calm.</i>

1009
00:43:01,245 --> 00:43:02,079
<i>So…</i>

1010
00:43:02,746 --> 00:43:04,873
<i>I'm not even sure if he noticed.</i>

1011
00:43:06,625 --> 00:43:08,460
It's my first time on a kayak.

1012
00:43:11,171 --> 00:43:12,089
This is fun.

1013
00:43:12,631 --> 00:43:13,924
I'm having fun already.

1014
00:43:14,592 --> 00:43:17,261
Oh, we need to row
in the opposite direction.

1015
00:43:17,344 --> 00:43:19,179
-One, two…
-Two…

1016
00:43:19,763 --> 00:43:20,848
Like this.

1017
00:43:20,931 --> 00:43:22,725
-You're good.
-I've got it.

1018
00:43:22,808 --> 00:43:23,767
One, two…

1019
00:43:23,851 --> 00:43:25,227
You're good at this.

1020
00:43:25,811 --> 00:43:26,937
I've got the hang of it.

1021
00:43:29,690 --> 00:43:30,649
Now, from that side…

1022
00:43:31,609 --> 00:43:32,484
This is fun.

1023
00:43:33,527 --> 00:43:35,321
-It's so fun.
-It is.

1024
00:43:37,072 --> 00:43:39,074
Can I ask why you brought scissors?

1025
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:42,286
The reason why I brought scissors

1026
00:43:43,037 --> 00:43:44,413
-is because--
-Let me guess.

1027
00:43:44,496 --> 00:43:45,372
Okay.

1028
00:43:46,040 --> 00:43:47,374
You're a scissors fanatic.

1029
00:43:48,375 --> 00:43:50,669
So you collect scissors as a hobby.

1030
00:43:51,503 --> 00:43:53,589
That's a reasonable guess.

1031
00:43:53,672 --> 00:43:54,757
-But that's not it.
-It's not?

1032
00:43:54,840 --> 00:43:57,635
My second guess is that
it's because you have a sharp edge.

1033
00:43:58,427 --> 00:43:59,553
You guessed right.

1034
00:43:59,637 --> 00:44:01,930
-So you can be quick to cut people off.
-Yes.

1035
00:44:02,973 --> 00:44:05,768
I tend to be quite guarded
in relationships.

1036
00:44:06,518 --> 00:44:07,770
-I don't trust easily.
-I get that.

1037
00:44:08,854 --> 00:44:11,315
And when someone tries to get close to me,

1038
00:44:11,398 --> 00:44:12,775
I get suspicious

1039
00:44:12,858 --> 00:44:15,194
about why they're acting interested

1040
00:44:15,903 --> 00:44:17,821
-when they barely know me.
-You question their motives.

1041
00:44:17,905 --> 00:44:21,200
I'd wonder why they want
to get to know me.

1042
00:44:23,202 --> 00:44:24,912
-So I'm a bit worried.
-Why?

1043
00:44:26,330 --> 00:44:28,165
People don't know this about me.

1044
00:44:28,248 --> 00:44:30,125
They think you're very friendly?

1045
00:44:30,209 --> 00:44:32,920
Yeah, they think I'm very sociable.

1046
00:44:34,088 --> 00:44:36,256
Isn't that kind of a hidden charm?

1047
00:44:38,592 --> 00:44:39,677
Because…

1048
00:44:40,511 --> 00:44:44,348
Rather than a guy who is nice to everyone…

1049
00:44:46,016 --> 00:44:49,853
I think if a guy has a cold side,

1050
00:44:50,479 --> 00:44:51,605
that can be attractive too.

1051
00:44:51,689 --> 00:44:53,023
-Really?
-Yeah.

1052
00:44:53,107 --> 00:44:56,402
Yeah, I think it can be
a very attractive quality.

1053
00:44:58,487 --> 00:45:01,156
<i>I always felt</i>
<i>a bit self-conscious about it,</i>

1054
00:45:01,740 --> 00:45:04,910
so I was very grateful
that she saw it in a positive light.

1055
00:45:05,911 --> 00:45:09,289
It did make me a bit worried

1056
00:45:09,790 --> 00:45:11,708
because I can also be quite…

1057
00:45:12,376 --> 00:45:16,046
I can be very easygoing
until something feels a bit off.

1058
00:45:16,130 --> 00:45:18,215
Then I just cut them off
without hesitation.

1059
00:45:18,298 --> 00:45:21,135
It made me think
that at the first sign of trouble,

1060
00:45:21,218 --> 00:45:23,429
we might both just cut and run,

1061
00:45:23,512 --> 00:45:27,975
or he could cut me off.

1062
00:45:28,058 --> 00:45:29,768
Is she seeing into the future?

1063
00:45:29,852 --> 00:45:32,229
-Why do I feel weirdly anxious?
-Right?

1064
00:45:37,693 --> 00:45:38,610
<i>It's the age reveal.</i>

1065
00:45:38,694 --> 00:45:39,945
<i>Let's find out their ages.</i>

1066
00:45:40,028 --> 00:45:40,863
<i>Here we go.</i>

1067
00:45:40,946 --> 00:45:42,739
REVEAL YOUR AGE TO YOUR DATE

1068
00:45:45,659 --> 00:45:48,078
I'm so nervous
now that I have to tell you.

1069
00:45:48,162 --> 00:45:49,997
-Same.
-Shall we guess first?

1070
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:50,914
Good idea.

1071
00:45:50,998 --> 00:45:52,708
I think you're 25 or 26.

1072
00:45:53,709 --> 00:45:54,626
I'm 27 years old.

1073
00:45:54,710 --> 00:45:55,794
You're 27 years old?

1074
00:45:57,379 --> 00:45:58,213
You look younger.

1075
00:45:58,297 --> 00:45:59,590
-Do I?
-Yeah.

1076
00:46:00,299 --> 00:46:02,134
Don't I look older?

1077
00:46:02,217 --> 00:46:03,719
-No, not at all.
-Really?

1078
00:46:03,802 --> 00:46:05,053
I'm 31 years old.

1079
00:46:07,556 --> 00:46:08,599
You look much younger.

1080
00:46:08,682 --> 00:46:10,100
Really? So we both look younger.

1081
00:46:10,184 --> 00:46:11,435
I guess so.

1082
00:46:12,436 --> 00:46:14,229
So you were born in 1995?

1083
00:46:14,313 --> 00:46:15,272
It's a four-year age gap.

1084
00:46:18,275 --> 00:46:19,109
I see.

1085
00:46:20,611 --> 00:46:22,696
-Why do I feel shy now that we know?
-Right?

1086
00:46:23,322 --> 00:46:24,531
It's a bit…

1087
00:46:27,701 --> 00:46:30,120
-So you were born in 1995.
-Yes, I was.

1088
00:46:30,204 --> 00:46:33,457
-Gosh, look at those dimples.
-Oh, Hyuk-joon!

1089
00:46:33,540 --> 00:46:35,167
Look how deep those dimples are.

1090
00:46:35,250 --> 00:46:37,211
They say four years is the ideal age gap.

1091
00:46:37,294 --> 00:46:39,046
I bet he thinks it's fate, once again.

1092
00:46:46,345 --> 00:46:48,305
-How interesting.
-Right?

1093
00:46:51,683 --> 00:46:53,560
There's something else I wanted to know.

1094
00:46:56,188 --> 00:46:57,022
What is it?

1095
00:46:57,105 --> 00:47:00,692
Is there someone
you have no interest in at all?

1096
00:47:03,946 --> 00:47:04,988
Not just one or two.

1097
00:47:07,366 --> 00:47:08,951
She's feisty.

1098
00:47:09,743 --> 00:47:12,287
-Really?
-Yeah, so many aren't my type.

1099
00:47:12,371 --> 00:47:14,873
I'm only going on dates
with the ones who are.

1100
00:47:16,166 --> 00:47:17,668
As for the others… I don't care.

1101
00:47:18,627 --> 00:47:19,711
What about you?

1102
00:47:21,838 --> 00:47:23,715
-I bet there's none.
-There is.

1103
00:47:23,799 --> 00:47:25,133
-Really?
-Yeah.

1104
00:47:25,884 --> 00:47:29,179
There's someone I know
I'll be a bad match with for sure.

1105
00:47:29,263 --> 00:47:30,597
-Really?
-Yeah.

1106
00:47:31,390 --> 00:47:33,517
Su-ji isn't my type.

1107
00:47:34,685 --> 00:47:35,602
Why not?

1108
00:47:36,603 --> 00:47:37,437
Just…

1109
00:47:39,731 --> 00:47:41,567
If someone acts quite young…

1110
00:47:41,650 --> 00:47:44,111
If they seem immature when they talk,
I don't feel attracted.

1111
00:47:46,530 --> 00:47:48,824
To me, Su-ji was actually…

1112
00:47:50,158 --> 00:47:52,244
-the biggest threat.
-Why?

1113
00:47:53,870 --> 00:47:55,122
She's just so pretty.

1114
00:47:55,205 --> 00:47:58,875
She's the kind of beauty I aspire to.

1115
00:47:58,959 --> 00:48:02,713
And I just learned yesterday

1116
00:48:03,297 --> 00:48:04,965
that we wear the same perfume.

1117
00:48:06,174 --> 00:48:08,844
So I thought, "I'm in trouble."

1118
00:48:09,469 --> 00:48:10,929
She thought she was in trouble.

1119
00:48:11,555 --> 00:48:13,181
She must see her as competition.

1120
00:48:14,391 --> 00:48:17,603
But I didn't notice that, it means…

1121
00:48:19,730 --> 00:48:20,856
Like, at all…

1122
00:48:22,107 --> 00:48:23,817
Have you been to the Post Office?

1123
00:48:24,401 --> 00:48:25,485
Yeah, I have.

1124
00:48:26,903 --> 00:48:28,530
Have you received a gift from anyone?

1125
00:48:28,614 --> 00:48:30,198
No, I haven't.

1126
00:48:31,742 --> 00:48:32,659
Have you?

1127
00:48:35,996 --> 00:48:36,830
I haven't checked.

1128
00:48:36,913 --> 00:48:38,040
-You haven't?
-No.

1129
00:48:39,583 --> 00:48:40,542
What?

1130
00:48:41,043 --> 00:48:43,253
-She did check her gift this morning.
-Yeah, she did.

1131
00:48:44,171 --> 00:48:46,048
<i>Is it from Hyuk-joon?</i>

1132
00:48:46,131 --> 00:48:47,674
It's a bit confusing.

1133
00:48:47,758 --> 00:48:51,720
I'm still not sure who it's from.

1134
00:48:52,638 --> 00:48:55,474
<i>I guess she's hiding it</i>
<i>because she's not sure yet.</i>

1135
00:48:55,557 --> 00:48:56,933
<i>But does she need to hide it?</i>

1136
00:49:03,732 --> 00:49:05,567
-Then do you have…
-Yeah?

1137
00:49:06,276 --> 00:49:10,238
Is there a certain way
you prefer women to dress?

1138
00:49:10,322 --> 00:49:11,615
-Fashion style?
-Yeah.

1139
00:49:11,698 --> 00:49:13,742
I don't think so,

1140
00:49:13,825 --> 00:49:16,078
as long as the way they dress suits them.

1141
00:49:16,161 --> 00:49:19,247
I think knowing how to style yourself

1142
00:49:19,331 --> 00:49:20,957
is an attractive quality.

1143
00:49:21,041 --> 00:49:22,209
I agree.

1144
00:49:23,001 --> 00:49:25,587
That's my hidden weapon.

1145
00:49:25,671 --> 00:49:27,881
-Really?
-Yeah.

1146
00:49:27,964 --> 00:49:31,718
What if you use that weapon on a date
with someone else?

1147
00:49:33,929 --> 00:49:35,764
I'll go and rip your clothes to shreds.

1148
00:49:39,643 --> 00:49:41,436
-Gosh, Hyun-seo.
-"Rip to shreds"?

1149
00:49:41,520 --> 00:49:42,813
She's not holding back.

1150
00:49:43,605 --> 00:49:46,400
-They're already acting like a couple.
-Yeah.

1151
00:49:46,483 --> 00:49:48,318
-She's acting jealous already.
-Right.

1152
00:49:48,402 --> 00:49:50,112
I'll go and rip your clothes to shreds.

1153
00:49:53,824 --> 00:49:54,908
Wow, mad respect.

1154
00:49:56,201 --> 00:49:58,829
What a thing to say. Wow.

1155
00:49:59,788 --> 00:50:01,206
I don't mind it.

1156
00:50:01,289 --> 00:50:03,542
I can handle it.

1157
00:50:09,715 --> 00:50:14,010
Before the date,
I just thought he was a decent guy.

1158
00:50:14,094 --> 00:50:15,637
But the more I got to know him,

1159
00:50:15,721 --> 00:50:18,432
the more I felt like we are a good match.

1160
00:50:18,515 --> 00:50:20,976
So I started to get butterflies.

1161
00:50:21,059 --> 00:50:22,561
But because of that…

1162
00:50:24,271 --> 00:50:25,564
I started

1163
00:50:26,440 --> 00:50:28,900
-being a bit awkward.
-That's how it goes.

1164
00:50:28,984 --> 00:50:30,694
It's very out of character for her.

1165
00:50:30,777 --> 00:50:32,320
It is.

1166
00:50:32,404 --> 00:50:34,030
<i>She must have suddenly felt</i>
<i>the butterflies.</i>

1167
00:50:36,074 --> 00:50:37,033
<i>She must really like him.</i>

1168
00:50:37,117 --> 00:50:39,369
<i>-You're right.</i>
<i>-She can't even look at him.</i>

1169
00:50:39,453 --> 00:50:41,705
<i>I can't look him in the eyes anymore.</i>

1170
00:50:44,499 --> 00:50:47,294
-I don't know. I feel a bit shy.
<i>-Oh my.</i>

1171
00:50:47,377 --> 00:50:49,963
-Oh my gosh.
-That's the feeling. That's exactly it.

1172
00:50:50,046 --> 00:50:53,008
This is the most invested
I've been on this show.

1173
00:50:53,091 --> 00:50:54,009
Look how I'm sitting.

1174
00:50:55,510 --> 00:50:57,804
They seem like a couple already.

1175
00:50:57,888 --> 00:50:59,181
Looking great, at least for now.

1176
00:50:59,264 --> 00:51:00,974
They're clearly in that stage

1177
00:51:01,057 --> 00:51:03,894
when your heart is racing
and you feel a bit shy.

1178
00:51:03,977 --> 00:51:05,187
-They are.
-And it's a slow burn.

1179
00:51:05,270 --> 00:51:06,646
-It's exciting to watch.
-It really is.

1180
00:51:06,730 --> 00:51:08,982
But I'm so curious because I feel like

1181
00:51:09,065 --> 00:51:11,026
if the tumbler was from Hyuk-joon,

1182
00:51:11,109 --> 00:51:12,736
he would've just told her it's from him

1183
00:51:12,819 --> 00:51:14,112
-during the date.
-Definitely.

1184
00:51:14,196 --> 00:51:16,990
-Hyun-seo is also usually quite upfront.
-She is.

1185
00:51:17,073 --> 00:51:17,908
Yeah.

1186
00:51:17,991 --> 00:51:20,535
But I think she kept quiet
because she doesn't think it's him.

1187
00:51:20,619 --> 00:51:22,370
-Just in case.
-She didn't want to ruin the vibe.

1188
00:51:22,454 --> 00:51:24,831
It could seem like she's boasting

1189
00:51:24,915 --> 00:51:26,917
-about a gift from another guy.
-That's true.

1190
00:51:27,000 --> 00:51:28,293
It's surprising

1191
00:51:28,376 --> 00:51:31,171
-how different each date was.
-It is.

1192
00:51:31,254 --> 00:51:33,507
Which couple do you think
was the most promising today?

1193
00:51:33,590 --> 00:51:35,634
-Do I even need to ask?
-It's obvious.

1194
00:51:35,717 --> 00:51:37,469
-The last one had the hottest spark.
-They did.

1195
00:51:37,552 --> 00:51:39,846
-Han-ju and Jin-woo showed some potential.
-That's right.

1196
00:51:39,930 --> 00:51:42,641
-Jin-woo's feelings are unclear.
-We need his side.

1197
00:51:42,724 --> 00:51:45,477
But Han-ju dropped a hint about twice.
She played it just right.

1198
00:51:45,560 --> 00:51:46,603
I agree.

1199
00:51:47,646 --> 00:51:49,314
<i>-Hello.</i>
<i>-You're back.</i>

1200
00:51:49,397 --> 00:51:50,482
<i>Hey.</i>

1201
00:51:52,734 --> 00:51:53,735
What did you get up to?

1202
00:51:53,819 --> 00:51:55,529
We made flower bouquets and stuff.

1203
00:51:55,612 --> 00:51:57,447
-That smells amazing.
-Are you going to join us?

1204
00:51:57,531 --> 00:51:59,616
-Do you want some <i>ramyeon</i>?
-Do you want some?

1205
00:51:59,699 --> 00:52:01,368
I'll just have one bite.

1206
00:52:01,451 --> 00:52:02,494
How was your date?

1207
00:52:02,577 --> 00:52:03,954
-It was fun.
-Really?

1208
00:52:04,037 --> 00:52:04,913
Yeah, we made liquor.

1209
00:52:04,996 --> 00:52:07,541
-How come you're so sober?
-I drank a bit.

1210
00:52:07,624 --> 00:52:11,336
Your date looks so flushed right now.

1211
00:52:12,337 --> 00:52:14,047
<i>Is Jin-woo all drunk?</i>

1212
00:52:16,007 --> 00:52:18,134
Hey, you're bright red.

1213
00:52:18,218 --> 00:52:19,594
What happened?

1214
00:52:19,678 --> 00:52:20,846
They went to a brewery.

1215
00:52:20,929 --> 00:52:22,222
Apparently, I reek of alcohol.

1216
00:52:22,305 --> 00:52:23,431
You do.

1217
00:52:23,515 --> 00:52:25,767
-We didn't drink that much.
-But I'm reeking.

1218
00:52:25,851 --> 00:52:28,019
Why do you seem so fine
when he looks like this?

1219
00:52:28,103 --> 00:52:29,104
He's a lightweight.

1220
00:52:29,604 --> 00:52:31,648
I can't handle my drink.

1221
00:52:33,358 --> 00:52:35,610
-Is everyone back?
-I think so.

1222
00:52:36,403 --> 00:52:37,404
Want a small bite?

1223
00:52:37,487 --> 00:52:39,364
-I just want a taste.
-Just a taste?

1224
00:52:39,865 --> 00:52:41,741
-What's this?
-Jeong-eun wants some too.

1225
00:52:42,325 --> 00:52:43,660
Shall we make you a plate?

1226
00:52:43,743 --> 00:52:44,953
-Shall we?
-We brought an extra one earlier.

1227
00:52:45,036 --> 00:52:45,912
Yeah, we did.

1228
00:52:53,378 --> 00:52:55,171
-What's this?
-What does it say?

1229
00:52:55,255 --> 00:52:57,591
AN ASSORTED FEAST AWAITS
AT THE SPARKS HOUSE

1230
00:52:57,674 --> 00:52:59,509
I didn't know there was a place like that.

1231
00:53:00,677 --> 00:53:02,637
<i>Gosh, compared to Season One…</i>

1232
00:53:02,721 --> 00:53:05,181
<i>They've really leveled up this season.</i>

1233
00:53:05,265 --> 00:53:07,392
<i>I wonder what kind of feast it is.</i>

1234
00:53:08,643 --> 00:53:09,853
<i>I hope I get to go.</i>

1235
00:53:10,478 --> 00:53:13,523
It's just non-stop.
You'll run them into the ground.

1236
00:53:15,609 --> 00:53:18,820
They'll end up with canker sores.

1237
00:53:18,904 --> 00:53:20,530
-From all the activities?
-They'll need some oral gel.

1238
00:53:20,614 --> 00:53:22,908
-I'm dying.
-I mean…

1239
00:53:22,991 --> 00:53:24,993
They have no time to just sit and relax.

1240
00:53:25,076 --> 00:53:27,037
They're on a tight schedule.

1241
00:53:27,120 --> 00:53:28,246
Good stuff.

1242
00:53:28,330 --> 00:53:29,873
-Well done.
-Seriously.

1243
00:53:29,956 --> 00:53:31,958
I think you'll get to go
if you match with someone.

1244
00:53:32,042 --> 00:53:33,251
-If we match with someone?
-Yeah.

1245
00:53:34,377 --> 00:53:36,129
TEXT THE NAMES OF THE TWO WOMEN
YOU WANT TO GO WITH

1246
00:53:36,212 --> 00:53:37,547
What?

1247
00:53:39,507 --> 00:53:40,800
This is tough.

1248
00:53:40,884 --> 00:53:42,093
Two men?

1249
00:53:45,305 --> 00:53:48,433
<i>I thought, "What should I expect</i>
<i>from the Sparks House?"</i>

1250
00:53:48,516 --> 00:53:50,685
They were going to give us
the time to sit and talk.

1251
00:53:50,769 --> 00:53:52,854
<i>So, I did want to go.</i>

1252
00:53:59,694 --> 00:54:00,820
This is hard.

1253
00:54:07,160 --> 00:54:08,119
Hurry up and send it.

1254
00:54:11,498 --> 00:54:15,293
TWO MEN AND TWO WOMEN
WITH THE MOST VOTES WILL GET TO GO

1255
00:54:18,171 --> 00:54:21,508
Oh, you need the most votes to go.

1256
00:54:21,591 --> 00:54:23,426
You need to get the most votes.

1257
00:54:29,140 --> 00:54:31,309
MALE WINNER, LEE JIN-WOO (THREE VOTES)

1258
00:54:31,393 --> 00:54:32,477
<i>Jin-woo!</i>

1259
00:54:33,269 --> 00:54:36,022
<i>-It's Jin-woo.</i>
<i>-I knew he'd be very popular.</i>

1260
00:54:36,106 --> 00:54:37,232
I'm shocked.

1261
00:54:40,944 --> 00:54:42,445
MALE WINNER, AHN SEUNG-HYUN (THREE VOTES)

1262
00:54:42,529 --> 00:54:44,280
-Three for Ahn Seung-hyun?
-Seung-hyun!

1263
00:54:44,364 --> 00:54:45,824
-Seung-hyun.
-Seung-hyun?

1264
00:54:46,408 --> 00:54:48,535
Wait. The way you said that…

1265
00:54:48,618 --> 00:54:49,452
My bad.

1266
00:54:49,536 --> 00:54:51,079
"Ahn Seung-hyun"?

1267
00:54:51,162 --> 00:54:53,164
Seung-hyun got three votes? Okay.

1268
00:54:53,248 --> 00:54:55,125
They had to pick two people,

1269
00:54:55,208 --> 00:54:58,586
so he could've been
many people's second pick.

1270
00:54:59,295 --> 00:55:01,423
This show is full of surprises.

1271
00:55:01,506 --> 00:55:02,716
FEMALE WINNER, HAN SU-JI (THREE VOTES)

1272
00:55:02,799 --> 00:55:05,010
<i>-It's Su-ji.</i>
<i>-I knew it. She's Ms. Popular.</i>

1273
00:55:09,806 --> 00:55:11,975
<i>An Jeong-eun?</i>

1274
00:55:12,058 --> 00:55:15,562
FEMALE WINNER, AN JEONG-EUN (THREE VOTES)

1275
00:55:15,645 --> 00:55:17,480
This is a surprise.

1276
00:55:31,578 --> 00:55:35,957
YOU'LL SPEND THE NIGHT AT SPARKS HOUSE
PACK YOUR BAGS AND GO NOW

1277
00:55:36,041 --> 00:55:37,333
My goodness.

1278
00:55:37,417 --> 00:55:38,668
What?

1279
00:55:38,752 --> 00:55:40,879
Oh, we're spending the night there?

1280
00:55:42,047 --> 00:55:43,131
-Stay the night?
-Stay the night?

1281
00:55:43,965 --> 00:55:45,133
They'll stay the night?

1282
00:55:45,216 --> 00:55:47,635
Will they go to Paradise?

1283
00:55:47,719 --> 00:55:48,887
They get a whole night?

1284
00:55:49,512 --> 00:55:52,974
-Oh my.
-Oh, no. They can't handle this.

1285
00:55:53,058 --> 00:55:55,101
It's too hardcore for eternal singles.

1286
00:55:55,185 --> 00:55:57,228
Imagine knowing
your crush is in that house.

1287
00:55:57,312 --> 00:55:59,647
This has suddenly turned into <i>Love Island.</i>

1288
00:56:01,066 --> 00:56:02,275
What?

1289
00:56:02,358 --> 00:56:05,820
I sent a text with the names
of the two people I wanted to talk to,

1290
00:56:05,904 --> 00:56:07,822
but they'll be going away.

1291
00:56:09,032 --> 00:56:10,033
<i>I was a bit shocked.</i>

1292
00:56:10,658 --> 00:56:13,578
<i>I decided I'd just go to bed early.</i>

1293
00:56:13,661 --> 00:56:14,621
Have a nice time.

1294
00:56:14,704 --> 00:56:17,874
<i>Su-ji got the most votes,</i>

1295
00:56:17,957 --> 00:56:19,417
<i>so I was a little anxious.</i>

1296
00:56:19,918 --> 00:56:23,797
<i>They would be in a private space.</i>

1297
00:56:24,422 --> 00:56:25,423
<i>A whole night…</i>

1298
00:56:26,174 --> 00:56:27,467
It's pretty intense.

1299
00:56:36,226 --> 00:56:38,561
-Did you see the text?
-Yeah.

1300
00:56:40,480 --> 00:56:41,564
Oh my…

1301
00:56:41,648 --> 00:56:44,109
-Have a nice time.
-Have fun.

1302
00:56:47,487 --> 00:56:48,404
We need to go now.

1303
00:56:48,988 --> 00:56:50,573
-You need to go now?
-Right now?

1304
00:56:51,157 --> 00:56:53,284
Right this minute?
I didn't even get to eat.

1305
00:56:54,410 --> 00:56:55,829
<i>Su-ji's guys are…</i>

1306
00:56:55,912 --> 00:56:57,288
<i>-Yeah.</i>
<i>-They're dying inside.</i>

1307
00:56:58,915 --> 00:57:00,959
-Let's talk when you get back.
-Yeah.

1308
00:57:01,042 --> 00:57:02,460
-Let's get going.
-Let's go.

1309
00:57:02,544 --> 00:57:04,087
Who knows what could happen?

1310
00:57:05,755 --> 00:57:08,758
-Was it always there?
-I noticed it whenever we passed by…

1311
00:57:08,842 --> 00:57:11,052
<i>Han-ju is also uneasy.</i>

1312
00:57:11,136 --> 00:57:13,221
-I feel so taken aback.
-Me too.

1313
00:57:14,013 --> 00:57:15,431
-I didn't see this coming.
-Me neither.

1314
00:57:16,266 --> 00:57:17,183
What's going on?

1315
00:57:17,809 --> 00:57:20,061
I thought I had no chance.

1316
00:57:20,145 --> 00:57:21,980
-I was ready to dig into the <i>ramyeon</i>.
-Same.

1317
00:57:23,231 --> 00:57:24,816
I'd better cook some more later.

1318
00:57:25,942 --> 00:57:27,277
I didn't know how to feel about it.

1319
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:29,154
When the results were revealed…

1320
00:57:30,738 --> 00:57:32,073
I was taken aback.

1321
00:57:32,157 --> 00:57:33,658
I didn't get why I got picked.

1322
00:57:33,741 --> 00:57:37,662
I didn't read it properly
because I was sure it wouldn't be me.

1323
00:57:37,745 --> 00:57:39,497
But my name was there.

1324
00:57:39,581 --> 00:57:42,500
<i>It felt like a mistake.</i>

1325
00:57:43,168 --> 00:57:47,505
I've never been the popular guy.
I was always like a side character.

1326
00:57:47,589 --> 00:57:49,090
So it was pretty awkward.

1327
00:57:49,174 --> 00:57:52,552
Why are the popular ones
feeling so guilty?

1328
00:57:53,386 --> 00:57:55,388
-It's like they're going to jail.
-It's <i>Les Misérables</i>.

1329
00:57:55,472 --> 00:57:58,600
The participants on other shows
would be thrilled, but on our show…

1330
00:57:58,683 --> 00:58:00,643
They're not used to it.

1331
00:58:00,727 --> 00:58:03,104
I really couldn't believe it.

1332
00:58:03,188 --> 00:58:05,106
I can't believe
Seung-hyun got picked either.

1333
00:58:05,899 --> 00:58:09,110
I'm not really sure how this happened.

1334
00:58:09,194 --> 00:58:10,570
How do I put this?

1335
00:58:10,653 --> 00:58:14,824
I felt like I might have come across
as… as a try-hard,

1336
00:58:14,908 --> 00:58:16,951
so I felt, like, a bit embarrassed.

1337
00:58:19,496 --> 00:58:22,540
<i>Just the idea of going to the Sparks House</i>

1338
00:58:22,624 --> 00:58:24,459
<i>made me feel a little weird.</i>

1339
00:58:24,542 --> 00:58:26,961
<i>And since I was told to go there…</i>

1340
00:58:27,045 --> 00:58:28,630
It felt a bit

1341
00:58:29,130 --> 00:58:31,716
like things were moving a bit too quickly.

1342
00:58:32,467 --> 00:58:34,219
<i>Don't be silly.</i>

1343
00:58:34,302 --> 00:58:37,013
Why do we have to spend the night?
Seriously, why?

1344
00:58:37,096 --> 00:58:39,682
But I doubt anything will happen
since it's us.

1345
00:58:39,766 --> 00:58:41,434
<i>You never know what can happen.</i>

1346
00:58:41,518 --> 00:58:42,644
<i>That's true.</i>

1347
00:58:43,686 --> 00:58:44,604
I'm curious.

1348
00:58:44,687 --> 00:58:47,148
SPARKS HOUSE

1349
00:58:48,608 --> 00:58:50,360
-What's inside?
-I smell food.

1350
00:58:50,443 --> 00:58:51,861
-Something tasty.
-It smells delicious.

1351
00:58:51,945 --> 00:58:53,238
Oh my goodness!

1352
00:58:53,821 --> 00:58:55,657
-Look at all this tasty food.
-Sorry.

1353
00:58:55,740 --> 00:58:56,866
We set it all up.

1354
00:58:57,492 --> 00:58:59,202
-Wow.
-It's a lot, isn't it?

1355
00:58:59,285 --> 00:59:00,453
Look at all this.

1356
00:59:00,537 --> 00:59:01,621
-There's a lot.
-Oh my gosh!

1357
00:59:01,704 --> 00:59:03,665
It's like a birthday feast.

1358
00:59:03,748 --> 00:59:06,459
It looks so delicious!

1359
00:59:06,543 --> 00:59:07,794
There are two bedrooms here.

1360
00:59:07,877 --> 00:59:09,629
-Gosh, this place is amazing.
-It's so big.

1361
00:59:09,712 --> 00:59:11,422
-They're huge.
-The beds are huge.

1362
00:59:11,506 --> 00:59:13,466
-Seriously.
-Not like our other beds.

1363
00:59:13,550 --> 00:59:15,760
Aren't our beds like half this size?

1364
00:59:16,594 --> 00:59:18,513
It really is a huge feast.

1365
00:59:19,347 --> 00:59:20,807
-Shall we toast?
-Yes.

1366
00:59:20,890 --> 00:59:22,267
-I already took a sip.
-Cheers.

1367
00:59:22,350 --> 00:59:23,643
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

1368
00:59:24,352 --> 00:59:27,021
He got picked as the most popular guy,
but he's only wearing a T-shirt.

1369
00:59:31,150 --> 00:59:32,151
It all looks good.

1370
00:59:32,235 --> 00:59:34,571
-I think the tail will taste best.
-And it's easy to eat.

1371
00:59:35,738 --> 00:59:39,117
-Oh, there are four tails.
-One for each person.

1372
00:59:39,200 --> 00:59:40,702
-Thank you.
-Eat up.

1373
00:59:41,494 --> 00:59:42,537
Thank you so much, sir.

1374
00:59:43,454 --> 00:59:45,540
Are you being extra polite
since he's older?

1375
00:59:46,124 --> 00:59:47,417
-Shall I call you <i>nuna</i>?
-No, thank you.

1376
00:59:47,500 --> 00:59:48,334
You don't like that?

1377
00:59:48,418 --> 00:59:50,587
She switched to honorifics
all of a sudden.

1378
00:59:50,670 --> 00:59:52,839
I won't be able to see you
as a guy if you call me that.

1379
00:59:52,922 --> 00:59:53,840
Oh, right.

1380
00:59:54,716 --> 00:59:56,092
-I'll call you by your name.
-Okay.

1381
00:59:57,093 --> 00:59:59,887
So he needs to call Dr. Lee <i>nuna</i>.

1382
00:59:59,971 --> 01:00:01,139
But Dr. An…

1383
01:00:01,222 --> 01:00:03,975
She doesn't like that term,
so he'll call her by her name.

1384
01:00:04,058 --> 01:00:06,185
Pick your clinic wisely, Jin-woo.

1385
01:00:06,269 --> 01:00:08,354
-"Clinic."
-They're both Korean medicine doctors.

1386
01:00:08,438 --> 01:00:09,814
Who will you go to for acupuncture?

1387
01:00:09,897 --> 01:00:12,942
Who will you go to for Chuna therapy?

1388
01:00:13,026 --> 01:00:14,193
Oh, dear.

1389
01:00:17,488 --> 01:00:18,906
-Is it tasty?
-It's so good.

1390
01:00:24,621 --> 01:00:27,123
I never even imagined something like this.

1391
01:00:27,206 --> 01:00:28,625
-Same.
-Me too.

1392
01:00:29,292 --> 01:00:30,460
I was so surprised.

1393
01:00:31,044 --> 01:00:33,171
I thought if you matched with someone,

1394
01:00:33,254 --> 01:00:35,590
you might have dinner together
or something like that.

1395
01:00:35,673 --> 01:00:38,593
Everyone got a text,
so I thought everyone was paired up.

1396
01:00:38,676 --> 01:00:42,055
-I thought we could choose our dates.
-Yeah, same.

1397
01:00:44,724 --> 01:00:45,642
I'm curious.

1398
01:00:46,309 --> 01:00:48,936
Did you guys pick anyone in this room?

1399
01:00:49,020 --> 01:00:50,396
-That's the stuff.
-Play the Truth Game.

1400
01:00:50,480 --> 01:00:52,106
-Go on, do it.
-Good question.

1401
01:01:00,823 --> 01:01:02,659
-Who wants to go first?
-Is there at least one?

1402
01:01:02,742 --> 01:01:03,785
Who should go first?

1403
01:01:05,828 --> 01:01:06,788
I picked one of you.

1404
01:01:08,998 --> 01:01:10,625
<i>Oh, she picked Seung-hyun.</i>

1405
01:01:10,708 --> 01:01:12,168
<i>She picked Jung-yun and Seung-hyun.</i>

1406
01:01:12,251 --> 01:01:14,087
SU-JI PICKED JUNG-YUN AND SEUNG-HYUN

1407
01:01:14,921 --> 01:01:15,880
I picked one of you too.

1408
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:18,299
SEUNG-HYUN PICKED SOO-HYUN AND JEONG-EUN

1409
01:01:18,383 --> 01:01:19,801
<i>I picked Jeong-eun</i>

1410
01:01:19,884 --> 01:01:22,887
<i>because I had so much fun</i>
<i>on our date today.</i>

1411
01:01:23,471 --> 01:01:24,764
Suddenly?

1412
01:01:24,847 --> 01:01:26,182
I knew it.

1413
01:01:26,265 --> 01:01:27,433
She's suddenly his top pick?

1414
01:01:27,517 --> 01:01:29,143
And his reason for it is…

1415
01:01:29,227 --> 01:01:30,311
He really is something.

1416
01:01:30,895 --> 01:01:33,064
He switches at the drop of a hat.

1417
01:01:33,648 --> 01:01:35,817
-I mean…
-He has no loyalty at all.

1418
01:01:35,900 --> 01:01:37,485
It's like how I switch
my service providers.

1419
01:01:37,568 --> 01:01:38,695
His reasoning's so simple.

1420
01:01:38,778 --> 01:01:40,488
-He enjoyed the date. That's it.
-That's it.

1421
01:01:40,571 --> 01:01:44,450
It must be nice being Seung-hyun.
He falls for a new person every day.

1422
01:01:45,368 --> 01:01:47,704
Every day must feel new and special.

1423
01:01:47,787 --> 01:01:48,913
I bet it's fun to be him.

1424
01:01:48,996 --> 01:01:50,998
I want to know what Jin-woo's thinking.

1425
01:01:53,209 --> 01:01:54,168
I picked someone here too.

1426
01:01:55,545 --> 01:01:57,296
JIN-WOO PICKED SU-JI AND JEONG-EUN

1427
01:01:57,880 --> 01:02:00,174
<i>He picked them both.</i>
<i>He didn't pick Han-ju.</i>

1428
01:02:00,258 --> 01:02:03,136
<i>I picked Jeong-eun and Su-ji.</i>

1429
01:02:04,011 --> 01:02:05,638
<i>Since they both got voted in,</i>

1430
01:02:06,222 --> 01:02:08,558
<i>it felt like a good opportunity.</i>

1431
01:02:09,434 --> 01:02:10,810
But I personally picked

1432
01:02:10,893 --> 01:02:13,521
the people I haven't had
a chance to talk to.

1433
01:02:14,397 --> 01:02:16,190
I picked Hyuk-joon and Jung-yun.

1434
01:02:16,691 --> 01:02:19,318
<i>Out of the guys I hadn't talked to,</i>
<i>I was most curious about them.</i>

1435
01:02:26,951 --> 01:02:28,077
<i>Oh my.</i>

1436
01:02:28,161 --> 01:02:29,287
<i>Things are getting intense.</i>

1437
01:02:30,246 --> 01:02:32,290
<i>Whatever happens at the Sparks House</i>
<i>stays at the Sparks House.</i>

1438
01:02:32,373 --> 01:02:34,041
<i>Whatever happens here</i>

1439
01:02:34,125 --> 01:02:36,169
<i>-stays between us.</i>
<i>-It doesn't leave this room.</i>

1440
01:02:37,003 --> 01:02:38,212
What exactly do you plan to do?

1441
01:02:38,296 --> 01:02:40,131
Oh, no. What if they play Truth or Dare?

1442
01:02:42,717 --> 01:02:44,469
-What if?
-No way.

1443
01:02:44,552 --> 01:02:46,429
But the Sparks House is a great set-up.

1444
01:02:46,512 --> 01:02:47,472
-Yeah.
-It really is.

1445
01:02:47,555 --> 01:02:49,932
-They can talk through the night.
-A good chance to talk.

1446
01:02:50,016 --> 01:02:51,726
Wait, let's think about this.

1447
01:02:51,809 --> 01:02:52,935
-What's with the tone?
-Hyuk-joon…

1448
01:02:53,019 --> 01:02:56,439
Things are going well
between Hyuk-joon and Hyun-seo.

1449
01:02:56,522 --> 01:02:58,900
And Jae-seo's out of the running.

1450
01:02:58,983 --> 01:03:01,694
-Right.
-Tae-hoon is currently in limbo.

1451
01:03:01,778 --> 01:03:02,695
He's at risk.

1452
01:03:02,779 --> 01:03:05,782
Jung-yun is in a tricky position.

1453
01:03:05,865 --> 01:03:06,699
That's right.

1454
01:03:06,783 --> 01:03:08,576
It'd be nice if he could talk

1455
01:03:08,659 --> 01:03:10,119
-to Su-ji.
-Yeah, she likes him.

1456
01:03:10,620 --> 01:03:14,457
Since the four most popular participants
are at the Sparks House,

1457
01:03:14,540 --> 01:03:18,461
the remaining participants
have lost their chance

1458
01:03:18,544 --> 01:03:19,921
-to talk to them.
-That's right.

1459
01:03:20,880 --> 01:03:22,965
<i>-The vibe here is…</i>
<i>-It's not good</i>

1460
01:03:23,049 --> 01:03:24,425
<i>-in the Lounge.</i>
<i>-It's so glum.</i>

1461
01:03:24,509 --> 01:03:26,511
What do we do while we wait?

1462
01:03:28,638 --> 01:03:30,306
<i>I felt like I hadn't done a good job</i>

1463
01:03:30,389 --> 01:03:33,392
<i>as a game changer.</i>

1464
01:03:33,476 --> 01:03:35,728
<i>-Oh, he's the only game changer left out.</i>
<i>-The rest got picked.</i>

1465
01:03:38,773 --> 01:03:40,608
<i>They're all so down.</i>

1466
01:03:44,612 --> 01:03:46,239
Shall we talk about something
that would lift the mood?

1467
01:03:46,322 --> 01:03:47,907
Yeah, what do you have in mind?

1468
01:03:49,450 --> 01:03:51,953
Is someone at the Sparks House right now

1469
01:03:52,036 --> 01:03:54,288
anyone's current top pick?

1470
01:03:54,372 --> 01:03:56,707
<i>-Good question.</i>
<i>-Smart move.</i>

1471
01:03:56,791 --> 01:03:58,292
<i>What happens on that side</i>
<i>is their business.</i>

1472
01:04:00,962 --> 01:04:01,879
Youngest goes first?

1473
01:04:01,963 --> 01:04:03,256
Me first, then?

1474
01:04:03,339 --> 01:04:04,340
Great idea.

1475
01:04:04,423 --> 01:04:07,969
-Everyone's suddenly perked up.
-Right?

1476
01:04:08,052 --> 01:04:10,513
Go on, then. Is it yes or no?

1477
01:04:10,596 --> 01:04:12,348
-Jumping straight in.
-You're asking me first?

1478
01:04:12,431 --> 01:04:13,975
Wow.

1479
01:04:14,058 --> 01:04:15,893
So much for the youngest going first.

1480
01:04:15,977 --> 01:04:17,895
-I had to act fast.
-Is that right?

1481
01:04:17,979 --> 01:04:19,856
-So you can end it before your turn?
-It must be yes.

1482
01:04:19,939 --> 01:04:21,232
-Nope.
-No?

1483
01:04:22,024 --> 01:04:24,402
JAE-SEO PICKED SEO-YOON AND HAN-JU

1484
01:04:25,444 --> 01:04:26,904
<i>That means his top pick is in the room.</i>

1485
01:04:26,988 --> 01:04:29,365
He spoke with such swagger.

1486
01:04:30,408 --> 01:04:33,744
"What's with the sudden questioning?"

1487
01:04:35,204 --> 01:04:38,541
<i>I was interested in Seo-yoon</i>
<i>from the start.</i>

1488
01:04:38,624 --> 01:04:42,169
<i>So I was relieved</i>
<i>that she got to stay in the Lounge.</i>

1489
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:45,006
What about your top pick?

1490
01:04:46,257 --> 01:04:47,300
Mine is still here.

1491
01:04:48,384 --> 01:04:49,343
<i>-Oh my.</i>
<i>-It's a secret code</i>

1492
01:04:49,427 --> 01:04:52,054
<i>-just between the two of them.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

1493
01:04:52,138 --> 01:04:55,933
I feel more certain about Hyun-seo now.

1494
01:04:56,017 --> 01:04:58,644
<i>As for Soo-hyun,</i>
<i>she never crossed my mind before,</i>

1495
01:04:58,728 --> 01:05:01,772
<i>but I like her positive energy.</i>
<i>That's why I picked her.</i>

1496
01:05:03,858 --> 01:05:05,151
Mine's gone to the Sparks House.

1497
01:05:05,234 --> 01:05:08,446
TAE-HOON PICKED SU-JI AND JEONG-EUN

1498
01:05:08,529 --> 01:05:12,325
Su-ji was my date today,
so I picked her as a courtesy.

1499
01:05:14,160 --> 01:05:14,994
Mine too.

1500
01:05:15,620 --> 01:05:18,831
JUNG-YUN PICKED SU-JI AND HYUN-SEO

1501
01:05:18,915 --> 01:05:20,833
I hope you two won't end up crying.

1502
01:05:20,917 --> 01:05:22,627
-Seriously.
-These two?

1503
01:05:23,210 --> 01:05:24,211
-Shall we sleep together?
-Shall we?

1504
01:05:24,295 --> 01:05:26,464
"Sleep together"? What are you saying?

1505
01:05:26,547 --> 01:05:27,673
You can't pick each other.

1506
01:05:28,841 --> 01:05:31,093
It's because both our roommates left.

1507
01:05:32,428 --> 01:05:33,304
My top pick

1508
01:05:33,971 --> 01:05:34,805
is over there.

1509
01:05:34,889 --> 01:05:35,932
<i>Both her picks are at the Sparks House.</i>

1510
01:05:36,015 --> 01:05:37,433
SOO-HYUN PICKED JIN-WOO AND SEUNG-HYUN

1511
01:05:37,516 --> 01:05:39,143
Mine too.

1512
01:05:40,019 --> 01:05:41,604
<i>Seo-yoon picked Seung-hyun?</i>

1513
01:05:41,687 --> 01:05:42,813
<i>And Tae-hoon?</i>

1514
01:05:42,897 --> 01:05:46,233
I just picked the two people

1515
01:05:46,317 --> 01:05:48,569
that I haven't talked to one-on-one.

1516
01:05:51,030 --> 01:05:52,657
<i>It would've been nice</i>
<i>if Seo-yoon had picked me,</i>

1517
01:05:52,740 --> 01:05:56,369
but I didn't have my hopes up.

1518
01:05:56,452 --> 01:05:59,747
I was a bit disappointed,
but I kind of expected it.

1519
01:05:59,830 --> 01:06:01,123
To be honest…

1520
01:06:02,083 --> 01:06:05,086
I wasn't even upset
because I knew she wouldn't pick me.

1521
01:06:05,795 --> 01:06:08,506
Jae-seo is the sad side character.

1522
01:06:10,341 --> 01:06:11,509
Mine left.

1523
01:06:11,592 --> 01:06:14,762
HAN-JU PICKED JIN-WOO AND HYUK-JOON

1524
01:06:14,845 --> 01:06:18,724
I wouldn't have picked Jin-woo
if I'd known my vote

1525
01:06:18,808 --> 01:06:21,060
would send him to the Sparks House.

1526
01:06:21,143 --> 01:06:23,020
So I regretted it a little.

1527
01:06:23,104 --> 01:06:25,690
If I'd known what would happen,

1528
01:06:25,773 --> 01:06:28,484
I would have picked the guys

1529
01:06:29,485 --> 01:06:31,529
I'm least interested in.

1530
01:06:32,154 --> 01:06:33,739
Mine is still here.

1531
01:06:35,658 --> 01:06:37,827
HYUN-SEO PICKED JIN-WOO AND TAE-HOON

1532
01:06:37,910 --> 01:06:39,078
What?

1533
01:06:39,161 --> 01:06:40,287
-What?
-Wait. Time out.

1534
01:06:40,371 --> 01:06:43,207
-Hold on. Rewind.
-She picked Jin-woo and Tae-hoon?

1535
01:06:44,291 --> 01:06:48,004
I thought we had to eat
with the people we picked,

1536
01:06:48,087 --> 01:06:49,880
and I wanted
to enjoy the feast comfortably.

1537
01:06:49,964 --> 01:06:51,173
It's because…

1538
01:06:52,008 --> 01:06:53,843
I've been craving sashimi<i>,</i>

1539
01:06:53,926 --> 01:06:57,555
but I didn't want to stuff my face
in front of the person I like.

1540
01:06:57,638 --> 01:07:00,599
So when I was deciding who to choose,

1541
01:07:00,683 --> 01:07:03,060
I picked the two guys
I wasn't interested in.

1542
01:07:03,144 --> 01:07:08,024
<i>But the person I would want to go with</i>
<i>the most is Hyuk-joon.</i>

1543
01:07:08,774 --> 01:07:10,067
She was strategic about it.

1544
01:07:10,151 --> 01:07:11,736
She picked the guys
she had no interest in.

1545
01:07:11,819 --> 01:07:13,195
Oh, that's a relief.

1546
01:07:16,115 --> 01:07:17,575
Oh, man.

1547
01:07:18,117 --> 01:07:18,951
I want to go home.

1548
01:07:19,035 --> 01:07:20,286
-Why?
-No.

1549
01:07:20,369 --> 01:07:21,537
You can't leave me, roomie.

1550
01:07:21,620 --> 01:07:22,913
Want me to keep making a fool of myself?

1551
01:07:28,544 --> 01:07:30,379
Have you all been to the Post Office?

1552
01:07:30,463 --> 01:07:31,297
Yes.

1553
01:07:31,881 --> 01:07:32,965
I noticed there are tumblers.

1554
01:07:33,049 --> 01:07:34,300
I saw that.

1555
01:07:34,383 --> 01:07:35,593
Didn't you say you wanted one?

1556
01:07:35,676 --> 01:07:37,428
Yes. I should buy one.

1557
01:07:37,511 --> 01:07:39,346
-You can't buy it for yourself.
-Self-gifting.

1558
01:07:39,930 --> 01:07:41,682
Oh, right. You can only
buy one for someone else.

1559
01:07:41,766 --> 01:07:45,019
He kept saying he wanted a tumbler
to carry hot water in.

1560
01:07:45,102 --> 01:07:47,229
-It would be nice.
-Something like that, or…

1561
01:07:48,022 --> 01:07:48,898
What else was there?

1562
01:07:49,482 --> 01:07:52,068
Do they keep restocking the gifts?

1563
01:07:52,151 --> 01:07:53,110
I was wondering that too.

1564
01:07:53,194 --> 01:07:56,447
-I don't think so.
-I think it's first come, first served.

1565
01:07:58,783 --> 01:08:00,159
I'm so curious.

1566
01:08:00,242 --> 01:08:01,202
I should check it out.

1567
01:08:02,828 --> 01:08:04,205
And he's off.

1568
01:08:04,288 --> 01:08:05,331
I suddenly got curious.

1569
01:08:05,998 --> 01:08:07,958
Could someone have gifted an item already?

1570
01:08:08,042 --> 01:08:09,001
Already?

1571
01:08:13,172 --> 01:08:14,215
What's he doing?

1572
01:08:14,924 --> 01:08:15,800
Picking out a gift?

1573
01:08:16,509 --> 01:08:17,343
What's going on?

1574
01:08:18,344 --> 01:08:19,345
That's weird.

1575
01:08:23,557 --> 01:08:25,309
I think it's gone.

1576
01:08:28,270 --> 01:08:30,397
CHOI HYUN-SEO

1577
01:08:32,316 --> 01:08:33,901
LAST NIGHT

1578
01:08:34,985 --> 01:08:38,697
<i>I went to the Post Office</i>
<i>to get a gift for Hyun-seo.</i>

1579
01:08:38,781 --> 01:08:40,157
So it <i>was</i> from him!

1580
01:08:40,241 --> 01:08:42,618
But she said
she didn't go to the Post Office…

1581
01:08:44,662 --> 01:08:46,080
This is tricky.

1582
01:08:46,664 --> 01:08:47,748
Something practical…

1583
01:08:49,416 --> 01:08:52,086
<i>I've come down with a bit of a cold,</i>

1584
01:08:52,169 --> 01:08:56,799
<i>and I was worried Hyun-seo would catch it.</i>

1585
01:08:56,882 --> 01:08:58,592
<i>So I gave her a tumbler.</i>

1586
01:08:59,343 --> 01:09:00,511
I'll go for this one.

1587
01:09:01,929 --> 01:09:04,098
<i>I also wrote a letter.</i>

1588
01:09:04,181 --> 01:09:07,017
<i>But I didn't want to be cheesy</i>
<i>by writing too much,</i>

1589
01:09:07,101 --> 01:09:08,978
<i>so I kept it short.</i>

1590
01:09:09,520 --> 01:09:12,565
I chose green paper on purpose.

1591
01:09:12,648 --> 01:09:15,609
<i>She's mentioned that it was</i>
<i>her favorite color a few times.</i>

1592
01:09:15,693 --> 01:09:17,361
The day before that,

1593
01:09:17,444 --> 01:09:19,947
we saw some yellow flowers on our date,

1594
01:09:20,030 --> 01:09:23,534
<i>so I sealed the envelope</i>
<i>with a yellow flower sticker.</i>

1595
01:09:23,617 --> 01:09:25,619
<i>So I'm guessing she knows it was me.</i>

1596
01:09:28,873 --> 01:09:29,707
I wonder what happened.

1597
01:09:29,790 --> 01:09:33,085
Oh, this guy is a true romantic.

1598
01:09:33,169 --> 01:09:36,255
-He's baffled.
-He's worried someone stole it.

1599
01:09:36,922 --> 01:09:40,926
So why did he act like
he knew nothing about the gift?

1600
01:09:41,010 --> 01:09:43,262
Because Hyun-seo said
she didn't go to the Post Office.

1601
01:09:43,846 --> 01:09:45,347
-She told him she didn't get a gift.
-So…

1602
01:09:45,431 --> 01:09:46,515
It's all messed up.

1603
01:09:46,599 --> 01:09:48,893
-She could have just been honest.
-Right.

1604
01:09:48,976 --> 01:09:50,895
I think she was overthinking it.

1605
01:09:52,229 --> 01:09:54,315
Are any items in the Post Office gone?

1606
01:09:54,398 --> 01:09:55,357
There must be.

1607
01:09:55,441 --> 01:09:58,027
-I think there is.
-You think someone's already given a gift?

1608
01:09:58,110 --> 01:10:00,154
But wouldn't it be really obvious?

1609
01:10:00,237 --> 01:10:02,948
-If you carry it around…
-It'd be like showing off.

1610
01:10:03,032 --> 01:10:04,491
-If it's a tumbler…
-Exactly.

1611
01:10:04,575 --> 01:10:06,118
We would all notice a tumbler.

1612
01:10:06,952 --> 01:10:08,579
Can you imagine? So funny…

1613
01:10:08,662 --> 01:10:10,164
A tumbler?

1614
01:10:10,748 --> 01:10:12,625
<i>Now, she can't even carry it around.</i>

1615
01:10:12,708 --> 01:10:14,376
<i>It will be awkward now.</i>
<i>She missed her chance.</i>

1616
01:10:14,460 --> 01:10:17,546
The tumbler is such a noticeable item.

1617
01:10:17,630 --> 01:10:20,591
When I walked back with it…

1618
01:10:20,674 --> 01:10:23,552
EARLIER THIS MORNING

1619
01:10:24,178 --> 01:10:26,055
<i>People were coming out of their rooms.</i>

1620
01:10:26,138 --> 01:10:28,098
<i>So I hid it slightly out of sight.</i>

1621
01:10:28,182 --> 01:10:30,684
-Hello.
-You're back.

1622
01:10:31,644 --> 01:10:33,270
-Are you going to the Lounge?
<i>-She was so subtle.</i>

1623
01:10:33,354 --> 01:10:35,189
-Yes.
<i>-She used her left leg to hide it.</i>

1624
01:10:35,272 --> 01:10:37,942
I just want to grab something.

1625
01:10:38,025 --> 01:10:40,152
-Okay. I'll shut the door.
-Okay.

1626
01:10:45,157 --> 01:10:46,992
It was obviously

1627
01:10:47,076 --> 01:10:49,328
a tumbler from the Post Office,

1628
01:10:49,411 --> 01:10:51,747
so I figured someone had noticed.

1629
01:10:51,830 --> 01:10:55,501
Now that it's a hot topic,
it'll be even more awkward to use it.

1630
01:10:55,584 --> 01:10:57,336
Everyone will ask who she got it from.

1631
01:11:00,881 --> 01:11:01,840
We got a text.

1632
01:11:02,591 --> 01:11:03,968
Oh, it's a rotation date.

1633
01:11:04,051 --> 01:11:05,052
ONE-ON-ONE ROTATION DATE STARTS NOW

1634
01:11:05,135 --> 01:11:06,637
This means we get to talk to everyone.

1635
01:11:06,720 --> 01:11:08,430
Their schedule's so full!

1636
01:11:08,514 --> 01:11:09,515
No time for rest.

1637
01:11:10,140 --> 01:11:12,226
I'm telling you, they'll get canker sores.

1638
01:11:12,309 --> 01:11:14,478
"The One-on-One Rotation Dates
will now begin."

1639
01:11:14,561 --> 01:11:16,647
"You'll get ten minutes with each person."

1640
01:11:16,730 --> 01:11:18,274
But we're missing some people.

1641
01:11:18,357 --> 01:11:19,900
I guess they'll join us for this bit.

1642
01:11:19,984 --> 01:11:21,318
-Are we going?
-Us too?

1643
01:11:21,402 --> 01:11:22,861
<i>Oh, they're joining too.</i>

1644
01:11:22,945 --> 01:11:24,530
<i>-I like this.</i>
-There are six locations.

1645
01:11:24,613 --> 01:11:25,864
That means all of us, right?

1646
01:11:26,407 --> 01:11:27,741
We needed this.

1647
01:11:27,825 --> 01:11:29,118
-This is great.
-Yeah.

1648
01:11:29,201 --> 01:11:30,119
I'm so relieved.

1649
01:11:30,202 --> 01:11:31,745
<i>The men will wait at each location,</i>

1650
01:11:31,829 --> 01:11:33,497
<i>and the women will go to them.</i>

1651
01:11:33,580 --> 01:11:35,416
<i>Each date will last ten minutes.</i>

1652
01:11:35,499 --> 01:11:37,293
-Do we pick from here?
-I'll take this.

1653
01:11:37,918 --> 01:11:39,628
It has the numbers and the locations.

1654
01:11:40,754 --> 01:11:42,214
-Okay.
-Let's go.

1655
01:11:43,966 --> 01:11:45,759
<i>Oh, after they finish,</i>

1656
01:11:45,843 --> 01:11:47,469
<i>-they go back to the Sparks House.</i>
<i>-That's good.</i>

1657
01:11:48,262 --> 01:11:49,805
<i>-Now's the time!</i>
<i>-To express their feelings.</i>

1658
01:11:49,888 --> 01:11:50,723
<i>Right.</i>

1659
01:11:52,933 --> 01:11:54,643
<i>I was really glad</i>

1660
01:11:54,727 --> 01:11:57,771
<i>to finally get the chance</i>
<i>to talk to everyone.</i>

1661
01:11:57,855 --> 01:12:02,026
<i>I hadn't considered</i>
<i>talking to every single guy,</i>

1662
01:12:02,109 --> 01:12:05,821
<i>so I was excited and worried</i>
<i>at the same time.</i>

1663
01:12:05,904 --> 01:12:09,825
I was happy to get the notification
about the One-on-One Rotation Dates

1664
01:12:09,908 --> 01:12:13,454
because it felt like a good chance
to have a serious chat

1665
01:12:13,537 --> 01:12:15,539
<i>with each woman one-on-one.</i>

1666
01:12:15,622 --> 01:12:18,751
We could get to know each other
on a deeper level.

1667
01:12:19,251 --> 01:12:21,045
-Eternal singles need this.
-There's no time to rest.

1668
01:12:21,128 --> 01:12:22,254
-They need a push.
-They do.

1669
01:12:22,338 --> 01:12:25,132
-You need to make your feelings clear
-Yes.

1670
01:12:25,215 --> 01:12:26,508
-if you like someone.
-You do.

1671
01:12:26,592 --> 01:12:28,510
This is Jae-seo's last chance.

1672
01:12:28,594 --> 01:12:31,263
Jae-seo and Seung-hyun
can't afford to keep being so stiff.

1673
01:12:31,347 --> 01:12:33,557
-They need to be direct.
-Yes.

1674
01:12:33,640 --> 01:12:37,269
AGUNGI TEA ROOM

1675
01:12:40,564 --> 01:12:42,816
AGUNGI TEA ROOM
SEUNG-HYUN

1676
01:12:42,900 --> 01:12:47,029
<i>I didn't have a chance</i>
<i>to talk to Soo-hyun or Hyun-seo.</i>

1677
01:12:47,112 --> 01:12:50,074
<i>So I was glad to finally get that chance.</i>

1678
01:13:00,709 --> 01:13:02,669
-Hello.
-Hi again.

1679
01:13:03,295 --> 01:13:05,547
-We already did this earlier.
-I know, right?

1680
01:13:06,465 --> 01:13:07,549
This view is so nice.

1681
01:13:07,633 --> 01:13:09,009
-It's pretty.
-Yeah.

1682
01:13:12,846 --> 01:13:14,056
For you…

1683
01:13:14,139 --> 01:13:15,057
Was today…

1684
01:13:15,808 --> 01:13:17,643
Was today just so-so for you?

1685
01:13:18,227 --> 01:13:19,186
I felt a bit confused.

1686
01:13:19,269 --> 01:13:21,647
Really? In what way?

1687
01:13:22,314 --> 01:13:25,692
I wanted a chance to talk
with some of the other guys,

1688
01:13:25,776 --> 01:13:28,904
so it was a bit frustrating
that I didn't get that chance.

1689
01:13:29,488 --> 01:13:31,490
-But we have it now.
-Huh?

1690
01:13:31,573 --> 01:13:34,410
-This is that chance.
-Right, yeah.

1691
01:13:34,493 --> 01:13:35,327
Yeah.

1692
01:13:36,036 --> 01:13:37,413
What about you?

1693
01:13:37,996 --> 01:13:41,041
-Well, my first impression pick…
-Yes?

1694
01:13:43,168 --> 01:13:45,421
I don't think she's interested in me.

1695
01:13:46,463 --> 01:13:47,673
I think I can guess who it is.

1696
01:13:47,756 --> 01:13:49,258
-Really?
-Yes.

1697
01:13:51,552 --> 01:13:52,928
Who… Who do you think it is?

1698
01:13:53,011 --> 01:13:54,263
Isn't it Hyun-seo?

1699
01:13:55,139 --> 01:13:56,098
Huh?

1700
01:13:56,682 --> 01:13:57,683
Or is it Soo-hyun?

1701
01:13:58,267 --> 01:14:00,018
Oh, yeah, it's her.

1702
01:14:00,102 --> 01:14:01,186
Oh, right. It was Soo-hyun.

1703
01:14:01,895 --> 01:14:03,188
-Yeah.
-Give it a shot.

1704
01:14:04,815 --> 01:14:07,901
-Yeah, I've wanted to talk to her.
-This is a good chance.

1705
01:14:07,985 --> 01:14:09,236
-You think so?
-Yes.

1706
01:14:09,319 --> 01:14:11,572
-I'm serious.
-Yeah, but like…

1707
01:14:11,655 --> 01:14:13,365
Talking is…

1708
01:14:13,449 --> 01:14:16,076
-Like…
-Don't stutter so much like you are now.

1709
01:14:16,952 --> 01:14:18,328
-Okay?
-Yes.

1710
01:14:18,412 --> 01:14:20,664
-Put yourself out there.
-Okay.

1711
01:14:20,747 --> 01:14:21,832
Go up to her and say,

1712
01:14:21,915 --> 01:14:25,377
-"Hey, do you feel like a chat?"
-Okay.

1713
01:14:27,921 --> 01:14:30,132
-Is yours… Well…
-What?

1714
01:14:30,215 --> 01:14:32,009
-Can I ask this?
-Of course.

1715
01:14:32,593 --> 01:14:34,219
Of course, you can. Ask away.

1716
01:14:34,303 --> 01:14:35,971
I'm ready. I'm all ears.

1717
01:14:37,014 --> 01:14:39,558
-Is your top pick Jung-yun?
-Yeah, it is.

1718
01:14:39,641 --> 01:14:40,601
I thought so.

1719
01:14:41,185 --> 01:14:43,645
I've wanted to talk to him,
but I haven't had the chance.

1720
01:14:43,729 --> 01:14:46,982
I might be wrong, but…

1721
01:14:47,065 --> 01:14:48,484
-I think it'll work.
-What will?

1722
01:14:48,567 --> 01:14:50,068
I think you could hit it off.

1723
01:14:50,152 --> 01:14:52,696
-I feel--
-But my mind isn't set.

1724
01:14:53,322 --> 01:14:54,698
-What?
-I'm not set on him.

1725
01:14:54,781 --> 01:14:55,991
I just want to talk to everyone.

1726
01:14:56,074 --> 01:14:58,243
Okay, I get it.

1727
01:14:58,327 --> 01:15:00,037
-I just want to chat.
-Oh, I see.

1728
01:15:00,120 --> 01:15:01,622
-Sorry, but that's it.
-Okay.

1729
01:15:03,123 --> 01:15:04,416
-But for me…
-Yeah?

1730
01:15:05,042 --> 01:15:07,961
-I enjoyed our date yesterday.
-Same.

1731
01:15:08,045 --> 01:15:10,255
-And our chat over there.
-Oh, right.

1732
01:15:11,131 --> 01:15:12,132
-Really?
-Yeah.

1733
01:15:14,510 --> 01:15:16,553
-Did I say this that day?
-What?

1734
01:15:16,637 --> 01:15:17,804
That I worked at McDonald's.

1735
01:15:17,888 --> 01:15:19,306
Really? No, you didn't.

1736
01:15:19,389 --> 01:15:20,849
I worked there because I love burgers.

1737
01:15:20,933 --> 01:15:22,851
-Don't lie. Really?
-For real!

1738
01:15:22,935 --> 01:15:24,978
-Don't lie.
-I always got free burgers.

1739
01:15:25,062 --> 01:15:26,897
I loved it because I got to eat
burgers every day.

1740
01:15:26,980 --> 01:15:29,066
What? That's so funny.

1741
01:15:31,193 --> 01:15:32,152
What the heck?

1742
01:15:34,571 --> 01:15:37,533
<i>It was fun talking to Su-ji.</i>

1743
01:15:37,616 --> 01:15:39,409
<i>The time just flew by.</i>

1744
01:15:39,493 --> 01:15:42,120
I feel like she is…

1745
01:15:42,746 --> 01:15:45,749
<i>She has a kind of tomboy vibe,</i>
<i>and I like it.</i>

1746
01:15:47,042 --> 01:15:48,335
-We can do it.
-Yes.

1747
01:15:49,044 --> 01:15:50,587
-Say it.
-We can do it.

1748
01:15:51,797 --> 01:15:53,632
<i>-I think it'll be great.</i>
<i>-Wait, already?</i>

1749
01:15:54,716 --> 01:15:55,926
<i>That went by so fast.</i>

1750
01:15:56,009 --> 01:15:56,927
I'm off.

1751
01:15:57,010 --> 01:15:59,137
-Let's talk again. Bye!
-Oh, right… See you.

1752
01:15:59,221 --> 01:16:01,390
-Bye.
-What are you doing? Sit back down.

1753
01:16:05,352 --> 01:16:06,186
Come this way, ma'am.

1754
01:16:06,270 --> 01:16:07,938
Hello, pretty lady!

1755
01:16:08,021 --> 01:16:09,648
-Have a lovely time!
-Have fun!

1756
01:16:09,731 --> 01:16:10,732
Goodbye.

1757
01:16:10,816 --> 01:16:12,067
-See you again!
-Okay!

1758
01:16:15,988 --> 01:16:17,614
-Oh, hello.
-Hello!

1759
01:16:18,282 --> 01:16:19,408
Aren't you cold?

1760
01:16:19,491 --> 01:16:21,243
I took my jacket off
because it's too warm.

1761
01:16:21,326 --> 01:16:22,327
Are you cold?

1762
01:16:22,411 --> 01:16:23,829
-No, not at all.
-You sure?

1763
01:16:23,912 --> 01:16:25,706
No, I…

1764
01:16:26,790 --> 01:16:30,419
<i>I'd never talked to Soo-hyun properly.</i>

1765
01:16:30,502 --> 01:16:32,629
DAY 1
FIRST IMPRESSION VOTE

1766
01:16:32,713 --> 01:16:34,923
They were each other's top picks.

1767
01:16:35,007 --> 01:16:37,718
They were the only two
that picked each other.

1768
01:16:38,552 --> 01:16:40,554
<i>So I wanted a chance to talk to her.</i>

1769
01:16:40,637 --> 01:16:42,431
I wanted to get to know her the most.

1770
01:16:43,265 --> 01:16:45,309
Hello. It's our first time one-on-one.

1771
01:16:45,392 --> 01:16:46,226
It is.

1772
01:16:46,852 --> 01:16:48,020
How are you finding it?

1773
01:16:48,103 --> 01:16:49,438
-Is it going as you hoped?
-Huh?

1774
01:16:51,356 --> 01:16:52,733
Well, to be honest…

1775
01:16:53,358 --> 01:16:54,818
I wanted to talk to you, but…

1776
01:16:54,901 --> 01:16:56,945
-Really?
-Yeah, but…

1777
01:16:57,029 --> 01:17:00,032
I was disappointed
it didn't happen until now.

1778
01:17:00,115 --> 01:17:02,326
So I'm glad I got this chance.

1779
01:17:02,826 --> 01:17:04,328
What do you want to know?

1780
01:17:04,870 --> 01:17:05,912
Oh, well…

1781
01:17:13,587 --> 01:17:14,755
-Go on.
-Well…

1782
01:17:14,838 --> 01:17:16,423
-What is it?
-Hold on.

1783
01:17:16,506 --> 01:17:17,674
-Something I wanted to ask?
-Yeah.

1784
01:17:19,760 --> 01:17:20,594
Well…

1785
01:17:23,764 --> 01:17:24,973
This is so frustrating!

1786
01:17:25,849 --> 01:17:28,018
-I feel so suffocated.
-I wonder what he wants to ask.

1787
01:17:28,101 --> 01:17:31,855
I thought, "This is my chance."

1788
01:17:31,938 --> 01:17:35,734
But maybe because I'm into her,
I got, like, a bit tongue-tied.

1789
01:17:35,817 --> 01:17:38,028
Even I felt like I was… Yeah.

1790
01:17:39,196 --> 01:17:40,781
What's your ideal type?

1791
01:17:40,864 --> 01:17:41,740
Oh, well…

1792
01:17:41,823 --> 01:17:44,660
-I'd like a good fit personality-wise.
-Me too.

1793
01:17:44,743 --> 01:17:47,746
-I want someone I can banter with.
-Yeah, same.

1794
01:17:47,829 --> 01:17:48,955
You're the same, right?

1795
01:17:49,039 --> 01:17:51,124
Yeah, I am. But…

1796
01:17:53,585 --> 01:17:55,170
Yeah, I am.

1797
01:17:56,254 --> 01:17:59,424
I like people I can talk to comfortably.

1798
01:17:59,508 --> 01:18:02,177
If the conversation flows well…

1799
01:18:02,260 --> 01:18:03,595
-You feel chemistry?
-Yeah.

1800
01:18:05,681 --> 01:18:08,183
<i>Seung-hyun said he'd wanted to talk to me.</i>

1801
01:18:08,266 --> 01:18:10,894
I also felt the same way.

1802
01:18:10,977 --> 01:18:12,938
So I had a lot of questions,

1803
01:18:13,021 --> 01:18:15,107
but I didn't have the time
to organize my thoughts,

1804
01:18:15,190 --> 01:18:16,400
so I was talking a mile a minute.

1805
01:18:16,483 --> 01:18:18,110
But Seung-hyun talks quite slowly, so…

1806
01:18:18,193 --> 01:18:21,863
Some girls prefer
a tough guy or a softer guy,

1807
01:18:21,947 --> 01:18:24,032
and some like a mix of both.

1808
01:18:24,116 --> 01:18:25,450
And you can change your mind.

1809
01:18:25,534 --> 01:18:28,787
You might like a tough guy at first
then realize you like softer guys.

1810
01:18:28,870 --> 01:18:30,622
So that's my mindset.

1811
01:18:30,706 --> 01:18:31,623
-Really?
-Yeah.

1812
01:18:32,374 --> 01:18:33,917
I talk really quickly.

1813
01:18:34,000 --> 01:18:36,545
Yeah, I'm a bit shocked
by how fast you talk.

1814
01:18:36,628 --> 01:18:38,422
Yeah, I talk super fast.

1815
01:18:38,964 --> 01:18:40,132
Did you catch everything?

1816
01:18:40,215 --> 01:18:41,383
Of course, I did.

1817
01:18:42,050 --> 01:18:44,428
<i>I can't remember what we talked about,</i>

1818
01:18:44,511 --> 01:18:48,306
<i>but it didn't feel like</i>
<i>the conversation flowed very well.</i>

1819
01:18:48,849 --> 01:18:51,935
Soo-hyun is closest to my type

1820
01:18:52,018 --> 01:18:54,563
in terms of looks, but…

1821
01:18:54,646 --> 01:18:56,815
-But you ended up leaving.
-Who left?

1822
01:18:56,898 --> 01:18:58,525
You went to the other room.

1823
01:18:58,608 --> 01:19:00,152
What are you…

1824
01:19:00,235 --> 01:19:01,653
What are you talking about?

1825
01:19:01,737 --> 01:19:03,530
-The other room?
<i>-They're totally out of sync.</i>

1826
01:19:03,613 --> 01:19:06,450
-Didn't you go to the Sparks House?
-Oh, right. Yeah.

1827
01:19:06,533 --> 01:19:08,160
That's what I was talking about.

1828
01:19:08,243 --> 01:19:10,287
-Oh, that?
-Yeah.

1829
01:19:10,370 --> 01:19:11,830
<i>The conversation didn't flow</i>

1830
01:19:11,913 --> 01:19:14,791
<i>as well as I thought it would, so…</i>

1831
01:19:14,875 --> 01:19:16,543
AGUNGI TEA ROOM
SEUNG-HYUN AND HYUN-SEO

1832
01:19:16,626 --> 01:19:18,754
How was the Sparks House?

1833
01:19:19,254 --> 01:19:21,423
The rice cakes were really good.

1834
01:19:23,675 --> 01:19:26,261
Wasn't it supposed
to have a lot more things?

1835
01:19:26,344 --> 01:19:28,138
<i>And I thought there was a spark</i>

1836
01:19:28,221 --> 01:19:30,265
between me and Hyun-seo.

1837
01:19:30,348 --> 01:19:31,808
But over time,

1838
01:19:32,434 --> 01:19:34,311
I feel like that's faded a bit.

1839
01:19:34,394 --> 01:19:37,397
And since we keep going on dates
with different people,

1840
01:19:37,481 --> 01:19:40,192
I keep changing my mind
about who I'm into.

1841
01:19:40,275 --> 01:19:42,903
I know it's a bit flaky of me, but…

1842
01:19:43,612 --> 01:19:46,823
I picked Soo-hyun.

1843
01:19:47,449 --> 01:19:48,950
Hyun-seo is

1844
01:19:49,034 --> 01:19:51,703
my current top pick.

1845
01:19:52,370 --> 01:19:53,747
Jeong-eun.

1846
01:19:53,830 --> 01:19:54,831
I had so much fun

1847
01:19:55,499 --> 01:19:57,334
on our date today.

1848
01:19:57,417 --> 01:19:58,919
That's why I picked her.

1849
01:19:59,002 --> 01:20:00,879
<i>He keeps changing his mind.</i>

1850
01:20:00,962 --> 01:20:01,880
SEUNG-HYUN, MR. FLAKY

1851
01:20:01,963 --> 01:20:04,090
WHO IS YOUR CURRENT TOP PICK?

1852
01:20:05,342 --> 01:20:06,885
Right now, it's Su-ji.

1853
01:20:09,054 --> 01:20:10,680
-Respect.
-Just yesterday,

1854
01:20:10,764 --> 01:20:12,224
-you said it wasn't her.
-I'm in awe.

1855
01:20:12,307 --> 01:20:13,809
You weren't into her yesterday.

1856
01:20:13,892 --> 01:20:15,185
Up until last night…

1857
01:20:15,268 --> 01:20:17,896
He thought about giving
Hyun-seo the couple hat instead.

1858
01:20:17,979 --> 01:20:19,856
So why suddenly Su-ji?

1859
01:20:19,940 --> 01:20:23,109
I really don't get it.
He says he likes her tomboy vibe,

1860
01:20:23,193 --> 01:20:26,279
but her tomboyish charm
was on full blast yesterday.

1861
01:20:26,363 --> 01:20:27,906
He wasn't into her then.

1862
01:20:27,989 --> 01:20:30,951
I think he might be a bit slow
to recognize his own feelings.

1863
01:20:31,034 --> 01:20:33,620
For those of you watching this at home,

1864
01:20:33,703 --> 01:20:36,623
I hope you are
keeping up with his timeline.

1865
01:20:36,706 --> 01:20:38,458
We need a whiteboard to write it down.

1866
01:20:38,959 --> 01:20:40,210
NORAEBANG
HYUK-JOON

1867
01:20:40,293 --> 01:20:41,127
<i>Where is this?</i>

1868
01:20:41,211 --> 01:20:42,587
<i>-Is it the </i>Noraebang?
<i>-It is.</i>

1869
01:20:49,261 --> 01:20:50,303
<i>I was looking forward to it.</i>

1870
01:20:50,387 --> 01:20:52,681
<i>I wanted a chance</i>
<i>to talk with the other women.</i>

1871
01:20:52,764 --> 01:20:55,851
<i>I was curious to see</i>
<i>who would come by first.</i>

1872
01:21:04,067 --> 01:21:06,236
No way.

1873
01:21:06,319 --> 01:21:08,572
This is getting out of hand.

1874
01:21:08,655 --> 01:21:09,739
NORAEBANG
HYUK-JOON AND HYUN-SEO

1875
01:21:09,823 --> 01:21:10,949
Again?

1876
01:21:11,032 --> 01:21:12,033
It is never-ending.

1877
01:21:12,117 --> 01:21:13,869
This is crazy. Is this for real?

1878
01:21:13,952 --> 01:21:15,328
Stop pulling my leg.

1879
01:21:15,412 --> 01:21:16,955
How is my first rotation date…

1880
01:21:17,038 --> 01:21:18,832
<i>It can't be real.</i>

1881
01:21:18,915 --> 01:21:20,458
<i>Four coincidences?</i>

1882
01:21:20,542 --> 01:21:22,544
How do you explain that?

1883
01:21:22,627 --> 01:21:24,671
I wasn't even surprised anymore.

1884
01:21:24,754 --> 01:21:28,300
It was such a shock for both of us.

1885
01:21:28,383 --> 01:21:30,343
It was definitely a random pick,

1886
01:21:30,427 --> 01:21:32,220
but I got matched with him again.

1887
01:21:32,804 --> 01:21:34,264
<i>I couldn't believe it.</i>

1888
01:21:34,890 --> 01:21:36,016
-This is scary.
-What on earth?

1889
01:21:36,099 --> 01:21:37,726
Am I under some kind of spell?

1890
01:21:39,102 --> 01:21:40,854
You're not a production plant, are you?

1891
01:21:40,937 --> 01:21:42,731
Of course not. Never.

1892
01:21:46,610 --> 01:21:49,070
Is there a time limit?

1893
01:21:49,154 --> 01:21:50,030
Yeah, ten minutes.

1894
01:21:50,113 --> 01:21:51,823
-Then you rotate.
-It's so short.

1895
01:21:51,907 --> 01:21:52,741
Yeah.

1896
01:21:52,824 --> 01:21:55,285
Maybe it's good you're starting with me.

1897
01:21:55,368 --> 01:21:57,329
You can relax a bit.

1898
01:21:57,412 --> 01:21:59,122
I'm not sure about that.

1899
01:21:59,205 --> 01:22:00,999
No? Well…

1900
01:22:01,082 --> 01:22:03,543
It's our first time

1901
01:22:04,169 --> 01:22:07,797
talking one-on-one with other people.

1902
01:22:08,381 --> 01:22:11,426
The only person I've talked to all day is…

1903
01:22:11,509 --> 01:22:13,970
-It's me.
-Yeah.

1904
01:22:14,888 --> 01:22:17,891
I did worry about that.

1905
01:22:17,974 --> 01:22:20,560
You keep getting matched with me,

1906
01:22:20,644 --> 01:22:24,564
but you must want to talk
to some of the others.

1907
01:22:25,148 --> 01:22:27,943
There must be someone else
you want to talk to.

1908
01:22:29,569 --> 01:22:31,863
But I feel confident.

1909
01:22:33,657 --> 01:22:35,200
Go ahead and talk to someone else.

1910
01:22:35,283 --> 01:22:36,409
I don't mind.

1911
01:22:36,493 --> 01:22:37,577
It's kind of like…

1912
01:22:37,661 --> 01:22:39,162
-"Go on, then."
-Yeah, exactly.

1913
01:22:39,245 --> 01:22:41,331
"I bet you won't find anyone better."

1914
01:22:42,248 --> 01:22:44,584
As for the guys, I'm like,
"Yeah, good luck with that."

1915
01:22:51,007 --> 01:22:54,678
By the way, do the gifts get restocked?

1916
01:22:54,761 --> 01:22:56,554
Yeah, I think so.

1917
01:22:58,640 --> 01:23:00,892
Because I went by earlier…

1918
01:23:02,519 --> 01:23:04,187
You really didn't get anything?

1919
01:23:05,647 --> 01:23:06,481
Me?

1920
01:23:07,315 --> 01:23:08,566
I'm not sure.

1921
01:23:09,401 --> 01:23:10,860
-Why is she lying?
-Right.

1922
01:23:10,944 --> 01:23:11,987
Why would she?

1923
01:23:13,530 --> 01:23:16,533
But I feel like it would be so obvious.

1924
01:23:16,616 --> 01:23:18,201
-What's obvious?
-If you get a gift…

1925
01:23:18,284 --> 01:23:20,203
All the gifts are quite noticeable.

1926
01:23:20,286 --> 01:23:21,579
It'd be like, "Hey, I got a gift."

1927
01:23:22,455 --> 01:23:23,915
It'd be too noticeable to carry around.

1928
01:23:25,250 --> 01:23:26,292
<i>I got Hyun-seo</i>

1929
01:23:27,585 --> 01:23:31,006
a tumbler that she could use
to carry hot drinks in

1930
01:23:31,089 --> 01:23:32,757
so she could soothe her throat.

1931
01:23:32,841 --> 01:23:35,260
And I made it obvious it was from me.

1932
01:23:36,219 --> 01:23:38,888
But she didn't show any kind of reaction.

1933
01:23:38,972 --> 01:23:41,141
<i>I found myself thinking,</i>

1934
01:23:41,224 --> 01:23:43,435
<i>"Isn't she taking this too lightly?"</i>

1935
01:23:44,060 --> 01:23:45,562
<i>This is a bit…</i>

1936
01:23:45,645 --> 01:23:49,482
What did you do in the Post Office?
You left the Lounge to go there.

1937
01:23:49,566 --> 01:23:53,194
The cold medicine wore off a bit,

1938
01:23:53,278 --> 01:23:54,779
so I went to get some more.

1939
01:23:57,157 --> 01:23:59,242
You must be feeling
really under the weather.

1940
01:23:59,325 --> 01:24:00,827
Yeah, but it's okay.

1941
01:24:02,287 --> 01:24:03,621
YOUR TIME IS UP

1942
01:24:03,705 --> 01:24:04,873
Go and do the rounds.

1943
01:24:07,792 --> 01:24:08,960
Have fun.

1944
01:24:09,044 --> 01:24:10,045
Bye.

1945
01:24:14,049 --> 01:24:15,383
That's it?

1946
01:24:15,467 --> 01:24:17,177
The vibe's a bit off.

1947
01:24:23,058 --> 01:24:26,936
<i>I'm not confused</i>
<i>about my feelings for Hyun-seo.</i>

1948
01:24:27,437 --> 01:24:29,689
But the date aside,

1949
01:24:29,773 --> 01:24:32,358
I'm feeling a bit run down right now, so…

1950
01:24:32,442 --> 01:24:35,028
-I think we're getting a late start today.
-Okay.

1951
01:24:35,111 --> 01:24:36,821
-You have a cold?
-Yeah.

1952
01:24:36,905 --> 01:24:38,740
How's your cold? Do you feel any better?

1953
01:24:39,240 --> 01:24:41,451
Yeah, I feel a little better.

1954
01:24:41,534 --> 01:24:43,411
But I'm still a bit nasal.

1955
01:24:43,495 --> 01:24:44,746
You do sound congested.

1956
01:24:44,829 --> 01:24:45,830
-Right?
-Yeah.

1957
01:24:47,999 --> 01:24:49,334
<i>But it did make me wonder.</i>

1958
01:24:49,417 --> 01:24:50,502
<i>When you like someone,</i>

1959
01:24:50,585 --> 01:24:53,296
you hope they'll show some concern

1960
01:24:53,379 --> 01:24:55,465
if they see you cough or sniffle.

1961
01:24:55,548 --> 01:24:57,634
And I kind of hoped she'd notice.

1962
01:24:57,717 --> 01:25:01,137
But Hyun-seo seemed oblivious
about me being sick until I told her.

1963
01:25:01,638 --> 01:25:05,391
<i>I couldn't tell if it was</i>
<i>because she's that oblivious</i>

1964
01:25:05,475 --> 01:25:09,187
<i>or because she's not as interested</i>
<i>as I thought she was.</i>

1965
01:25:09,270 --> 01:25:11,815
<i>That weighed on my mind a lot.</i>

1966
01:25:11,898 --> 01:25:13,817
On top of feeling

1967
01:25:13,900 --> 01:25:15,318
a bit nervous yesterday,

1968
01:25:15,944 --> 01:25:19,197
I felt really unwell.
But I wrote her a letter early on,

1969
01:25:19,280 --> 01:25:22,117
and I gifted her the tumbler.

1970
01:25:22,700 --> 01:25:26,121
But I didn't want to say it out loud.

1971
01:25:27,247 --> 01:25:30,208
I feel a bit disappointed.

1972
01:25:30,291 --> 01:25:33,461
-I get how he feels.
-Yeah, it's upsetting she didn't notice.

1973
01:25:41,511 --> 01:25:43,388
-Hello.
-Hey.

1974
01:25:43,471 --> 01:25:44,597
<i>Hyuk-joon and Han-ju.</i>

1975
01:25:44,681 --> 01:25:45,765
What's that?

1976
01:25:45,849 --> 01:25:48,977
It's a pouch for storing
my makeup and stuff.

1977
01:25:49,060 --> 01:25:50,228
I have a hand warmer as well.

1978
01:25:52,188 --> 01:25:55,483
-It's our first time talking one-on-one.
-Yeah.

1979
01:25:56,151 --> 01:25:57,193
I really wanted this chance.

1980
01:25:57,277 --> 01:25:58,987
-Really?
-Yeah.

1981
01:25:59,070 --> 01:26:00,697
But until now,

1982
01:26:00,780 --> 01:26:04,284
all the dates were decided at random.

1983
01:26:04,367 --> 01:26:05,201
That's true.

1984
01:26:05,702 --> 01:26:07,954
We couldn't choose our dates.

1985
01:26:09,455 --> 01:26:10,415
But I wanted a chat with you.

1986
01:26:13,543 --> 01:26:15,336
But… Can I ask this?

1987
01:26:15,420 --> 01:26:16,462
Ask me what?

1988
01:26:17,755 --> 01:26:19,340
Who was your first impression pick?

1989
01:26:21,384 --> 01:26:22,886
I picked you.

1990
01:26:22,969 --> 01:26:23,803
-Me?
-Yeah.

1991
01:26:23,887 --> 01:26:24,929
-Really?
-Yes.

1992
01:26:25,013 --> 01:26:25,847
How come?

1993
01:26:27,015 --> 01:26:28,850
Your voice got so loud.
Are you that happy?

1994
01:26:29,434 --> 01:26:31,269
I'm just amazed.

1995
01:26:31,352 --> 01:26:33,479
Why did I choose you, you ask?

1996
01:26:33,563 --> 01:26:37,859
In terms of first impressions,
you were closest to my type.

1997
01:26:37,942 --> 01:26:41,196
You have a kind of bad guy vibe,
which is what I'm into.

1998
01:26:41,279 --> 01:26:44,407
When I first saw the four guys,
you were the closest to my type.

1999
01:26:44,490 --> 01:26:45,742
-Really?
-Yeah.

2000
01:26:45,825 --> 01:26:47,619
What an honor.

2001
01:26:50,955 --> 01:26:53,374
<i>I thought it was some kind of prank.</i>

2002
01:26:56,794 --> 01:26:58,004
Are we celebrating something?

2003
01:26:58,671 --> 01:26:59,505
That was random.

2004
01:27:01,216 --> 01:27:03,843
-Let's talk again if we get the chance.
-Okay.

2005
01:27:03,927 --> 01:27:05,261
-Bye.
-Bye.

2006
01:27:09,224 --> 01:27:11,976
I was shocked.
I thought she wasn't interested at all.

2007
01:27:12,852 --> 01:27:13,978
I wanted to talk to you.

2008
01:27:14,062 --> 01:27:15,146
-Really?
-Yeah.

2009
01:27:15,230 --> 01:27:16,314
It's nice to have this chance.

2010
01:27:16,397 --> 01:27:21,194
Your ideal type in your diary
was so similar to mine.

2011
01:27:21,778 --> 01:27:23,321
-You read my diary?
-Yeah.

2012
01:27:23,404 --> 01:27:24,948
You were a pretty cute baby.

2013
01:27:28,534 --> 01:27:30,912
Wait. Can I step out for a moment?

2014
01:27:31,788 --> 01:27:35,625
<i>When I found out that so many had picked</i>
<i>me for the first impression vote and all,</i>

2015
01:27:36,209 --> 01:27:38,962
I thought maybe
I'd made up my mind too soon.

2016
01:27:39,545 --> 01:27:43,091
<i>Everyone is so charming and attractive.</i>

2017
01:27:44,092 --> 01:27:45,051
<i>So…</i>

2018
01:27:47,845 --> 01:27:51,057
Maybe it wouldn't be so bad
for me to open up

2019
01:27:51,140 --> 01:27:53,059
to more people.

2020
01:28:55,121 --> 01:28:57,123
Subtitle translation by: Hannah Og Nam
